397 /// Top-level MachineScheduler pass driver. ----
398 /// ----
399 /// Visit blocks in function order. Divide each block into scheduling regions ----
400 /// and visit them bottom-up. Visiting regions bottom-up is not required, but is ----
401 /// consistent with the DAG builder, which traverses the interior of the ----
402 /// scheduling regions bottom-up. ----
403 /// ----
404 /// This design avoids exposing scheduling boundaries to the DAG builder, ----
405 /// simplifying the DAG builder's support for "special" target instructions. ----
406 /// At the same time the design allows target schedulers to operate across ----
407 /// scheduling boundaries, for example to bundle the boundary instructions ----
408 /// without reordering them. This creates complexity, because the target ----
409 /// scheduler must update the RegionBegin and RegionEnd positions cached by ----
410 /// ScheduleDAGInstrs whenever adding or removing instructions. A much simpler ----
411 /// design would be to split blocks at scheduling boundaries, but LLVM has a ----
412 /// general bias against block splitting purely for implementation simplicity. ----
413 bool MachineScheduler::runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &mf) { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
414 if (skipFunction(mf.getFunction())) 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
415 return false; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
416 ----
417 if (EnableMachineSched.getNumOccurrences()) { 0
418 if (!EnableMachineSched) 0
419 return false; 0
420 } else if (!mf.getSubtarget().enableMachineScheduler()) 0
421 return false; 0
422 ----
423 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Before MISched:\n"; mf.print(dbgs())); 0
424 ----
425 // Initialize the context of the pass. ----
426 MF = &mf; 0
427 MLI = &getAnalysis(); 0
428 MDT = &getAnalysis(); 0
429 PassConfig = &getAnalysis(); 0
430 AA = &getAnalysis().getAAResults(); 0
431 ----
432 LIS = &getAnalysis(); 0
433 ----
434 if (VerifyScheduling) { 0
435 LLVM_DEBUG(LIS->dump()); 0
436 MF->verify(this, "Before machine scheduling."); 0
437 } ----
438 RegClassInfo->runOnMachineFunction(*MF); 0
439 ----
440 // Instantiate the selected scheduler for this target, function, and ----
441 // optimization level. ----
442 std::unique_ptr Scheduler(createMachineScheduler()); 0
443 scheduleRegions(*Scheduler, false); 0
444 ----
445 LLVM_DEBUG(LIS->dump()); 0
446 if (VerifyScheduling) 0
447 MF->verify(this, "After machine scheduling."); 0
448 return true; 0
449 } 0

453 return false; 0

482 ----
483 /// Return true of the given instruction should not be included in a scheduling ----
484 /// region. ----
485 /// ----
486 /// MachineScheduler does not currently support scheduling across calls. To ----
487 /// handle calls, the DAG builder needs to be modified to create register ----
488 /// anti/output dependencies on the registers clobbered by the call's regmask ----
489 /// operand. In PreRA scheduling, the stack pointer adjustment already prevents ----
490 /// scheduling across calls. In PostRA scheduling, we need the isCall to enforce ----
491 /// the boundary, but there would be no benefit to postRA scheduling across ----
492 /// calls this late anyway. ----
493 static bool isSchedBoundary(MachineBasicBlock::iterator MI, 0
494 MachineBasicBlock *MBB, ----
495 MachineFunction *MF, ----
496 const TargetInstrInfo *TII) { ----
497 return MI->isCall() || TII->isSchedulingBoundary(*MI, MBB, *MF); 0
498 } ----
499 ----
500 /// A region of an MBB for scheduling. ----
501 namespace { ----
502 struct SchedRegion { ----
503 /// RegionBegin is the first instruction in the scheduling region, and ----
504 /// RegionEnd is either MBB->end() or the scheduling boundary after the ----
505 /// last instruction in the scheduling region. These iterators cannot refer ----
506 /// to instructions outside of the identified scheduling region because ----
507 /// those may be reordered before scheduling this region. ----
508 MachineBasicBlock::iterator RegionBegin; ----
509 MachineBasicBlock::iterator RegionEnd; ----
510 unsigned NumRegionInstrs; ----
511 ----
512 SchedRegion(MachineBasicBlock::iterator B, MachineBasicBlock::iterator E, 0
513 unsigned N) : ----
514 RegionBegin(B), RegionEnd(E), NumRegionInstrs(N) {} 0
515 }; ----
516 } // end anonymous namespace ----
517 ----
518 using MBBRegionsVector = SmallVector; ----
519 ----
520 static void ----
521 getSchedRegions(MachineBasicBlock *MBB, 0
522 MBBRegionsVector &Regions, ----
523 bool RegionsTopDown) { ----
524 MachineFunction *MF = MBB->getParent(); 0
525 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = MF->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo(); 0
526 ----
527 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I = nullptr; 0
528 for(MachineBasicBlock::iterator RegionEnd = MBB->end(); 0
529 RegionEnd != MBB->begin(); RegionEnd = I) { 0
530 ----
531 // Avoid decrementing RegionEnd for blocks with no terminator. ----
532 if (RegionEnd != MBB->end() || 0
533 isSchedBoundary(&*std::prev(RegionEnd), &*MBB, MF, TII)) { 0
534 --RegionEnd; 0
535 } ----
536 ----
537 // The next region starts above the previous region. Look backward in the ----
538 // instruction stream until we find the nearest boundary. ----
539 unsigned NumRegionInstrs = 0; 0
540 I = RegionEnd; 0
541 for (;I != MBB->begin(); --I) { 0
542 MachineInstr &MI = *std::prev(I); 0
543 if (isSchedBoundary(&MI, &*MBB, MF, TII)) 0
544 break; 0
545 if (!MI.isDebugOrPseudoInstr()) { 0
546 // MBB::size() uses instr_iterator to count. Here we need a bundle to ----
547 // count as a single instruction. ----
548 ++NumRegionInstrs; 0
549 } ----
550 } ----
551 ----
552 // It's possible we found a scheduling region that only has debug ----
553 // instructions. Don't bother scheduling these. ----
554 if (NumRegionInstrs != 0) 0
555 Regions.push_back(SchedRegion(I, RegionEnd, NumRegionInstrs)); 0
556 } ----
557 ----
558 if (RegionsTopDown) 0
559 std::reverse(Regions.begin(), Regions.end()); 0
560 } 0

562 /// Main driver for both MachineScheduler and PostMachineScheduler. ----
563 void MachineSchedulerBase::scheduleRegions(ScheduleDAGInstrs &Scheduler, 0
564 bool FixKillFlags) { ----
565 // Visit all machine basic blocks. ----
566 // ----
567 // TODO: Visit blocks in global postorder or postorder within the bottom-up ----
568 // loop tree. Then we can optionally compute global RegPressure. ----
569 for (MachineFunction::iterator MBB = MF->begin(), MBBEnd = MF->end(); 0
570 MBB != MBBEnd; ++MBB) { 0
571 ----
572 Scheduler.startBlock(&*MBB); 0
573 ----
574 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
575 if (SchedOnlyFunc.getNumOccurrences() && SchedOnlyFunc != MF->getName()) 0
576 continue; 0
577 if (SchedOnlyBlock.getNumOccurrences() 0
578 && (int)SchedOnlyBlock != MBB->getNumber()) 0
579 continue; 0
580 #endif ----
581 ----
582 // Break the block into scheduling regions [I, RegionEnd). RegionEnd ----
583 // points to the scheduling boundary at the bottom of the region. The DAG ----
584 // does not include RegionEnd, but the region does (i.e. the next ----
585 // RegionEnd is above the previous RegionBegin). If the current block has ----
586 // no terminator then RegionEnd == MBB->end() for the bottom region. ----
587 // ----
588 // All the regions of MBB are first found and stored in MBBRegions, which ----
589 // will be processed (MBB) top-down if initialized with true. ----
590 // ----
591 // The Scheduler may insert instructions during either schedule() or ----
592 // exitRegion(), even for empty regions. So the local iterators 'I' and ----
593 // 'RegionEnd' are invalid across these calls. Instructions must not be ----
594 // added to other regions than the current one without updating MBBRegions. ----
595 ----
596 MBBRegionsVector MBBRegions; 0
597 getSchedRegions(&*MBB, MBBRegions, Scheduler.doMBBSchedRegionsTopDown()); 0
598 for (const SchedRegion &R : MBBRegions) { 0
599 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I = R.RegionBegin; 0
600 MachineBasicBlock::iterator RegionEnd = R.RegionEnd; 0
601 unsigned NumRegionInstrs = R.NumRegionInstrs; 0
602 ----
603 // Notify the scheduler of the region, even if we may skip scheduling ----
604 // it. Perhaps it still needs to be bundled. ----
605 Scheduler.enterRegion(&*MBB, I, RegionEnd, NumRegionInstrs); 0
606 ----
607 // Skip empty scheduling regions (0 or 1 schedulable instructions). ----
608 if (I == RegionEnd || I == std::prev(RegionEnd)) { 0
609 // Close the current region. Bundle the terminator if needed. ----
610 // This invalidates 'RegionEnd' and 'I'. ----
611 Scheduler.exitRegion(); 0
612 continue; 0
613 } ----
614 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "********** MI Scheduling **********\n"); 0
615 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << MF->getName() << ":" << printMBBReference(*MBB) 0
616 << " " << MBB->getName() << "\n From: " << *I ----
617 << " To: "; ----
618 if (RegionEnd != MBB->end()) dbgs() << *RegionEnd; ----
619 else dbgs() << "End\n"; ----
620 dbgs() << " RegionInstrs: " << NumRegionInstrs << '\n'); ----
621 if (DumpCriticalPathLength) { 0
622 errs() << MF->getName(); 0
623 errs() << ":%bb. " << MBB->getNumber(); 0
624 errs() << " " << MBB->getName() << " \n"; 0
625 } ----
626 ----
627 // Schedule a region: possibly reorder instructions. ----
628 // This invalidates the original region iterators. ----
629 Scheduler.schedule(); 0
630 ----
631 // Close the current region. ----
632 Scheduler.exitRegion(); 0
633 } ----
634 Scheduler.finishBlock(); 0
635 // FIXME: Ideally, no further passes should rely on kill flags. However, ----
636 // thumb2 size reduction is currently an exception, so the PostMIScheduler ----
637 // needs to do this. ----
638 if (FixKillFlags) 0
639 Scheduler.fixupKills(*MBB); 0
640 } 0
641 Scheduler.finalizeSchedule(); 0
642 } 0
643 ----
644 void MachineSchedulerBase::print(raw_ostream &O, const Module* m) const { 0
645 // unimplemented ----
646 } 0
647 ----
648 #if !defined(NDEBUG) || defined(LLVM_ENABLE_DUMP) ----
649 LLVM_DUMP_METHOD void ReadyQueue::dump() const { 0
650 dbgs() << "Queue " << Name << ": "; 0
651 for (const SUnit *SU : Queue) 0
652 dbgs() << SU->NodeNum << " "; 0
653 dbgs() << "\n"; 0
654 } 0
655 #endif ----

657 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
658 // ScheduleDAGMI - Basic machine instruction scheduling. This is ----
659 // independent of PreRA/PostRA scheduling and involves no extra book-keeping for ----
660 // virtual registers. ----
661 // ===----------------------------------------------------------------------===/ ----
662 ----
663 // Provide a vtable anchor. ----
664 ScheduleDAGMI::~ScheduleDAGMI() = default; 0
665 ----
666 /// ReleaseSucc - Decrement the NumPredsLeft count of a successor. When ----
667 /// NumPredsLeft reaches zero, release the successor node. ----
668 /// ----
669 /// FIXME: Adjust SuccSU height based on MinLatency. ----
670 void ScheduleDAGMI::releaseSucc(SUnit *SU, SDep *SuccEdge) { 0
671 SUnit *SuccSU = SuccEdge->getSUnit(); 0
672 ----
673 if (SuccEdge->isWeak()) { 0
674 --SuccSU->WeakPredsLeft; 0
675 if (SuccEdge->isCluster()) 0
676 NextClusterSucc = SuccSU; 0
677 return; 0
678 } ----
679 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
680 if (SuccSU->NumPredsLeft == 0) { 0
681 dbgs() << "*** Scheduling failed! ***\n"; 0
682 dumpNode(*SuccSU); 0
683 dbgs() << " has been released too many times!\n"; 0
684 llvm_unreachable(nullptr); 0
685 } ----
686 #endif ----
687 // SU->TopReadyCycle was set to CurrCycle when it was scheduled. However, ----
688 // CurrCycle may have advanced since then. ----
689 if (SuccSU->TopReadyCycle < SU->TopReadyCycle + SuccEdge->getLatency()) 0
690 SuccSU->TopReadyCycle = SU->TopReadyCycle + SuccEdge->getLatency(); 0
691 ----
692 --SuccSU->NumPredsLeft; 0
693 if (SuccSU->NumPredsLeft == 0 && SuccSU != &ExitSU) 0
694 SchedImpl->releaseTopNode(SuccSU); 0
695 } ----
696 ----
697 /// releaseSuccessors - Call releaseSucc on each of SU's successors. ----
698 void ScheduleDAGMI::releaseSuccessors(SUnit *SU) { 0
699 for (SDep &Succ : SU->Succs) 0
700 releaseSucc(SU, &Succ); 0
701 } 0
702 ----
703 /// ReleasePred - Decrement the NumSuccsLeft count of a predecessor. When ----
704 /// NumSuccsLeft reaches zero, release the predecessor node. ----
705 /// ----
706 /// FIXME: Adjust PredSU height based on MinLatency. ----
707 void ScheduleDAGMI::releasePred(SUnit *SU, SDep *PredEdge) { 0
708 SUnit *PredSU = PredEdge->getSUnit(); 0
709 ----
710 if (PredEdge->isWeak()) { 0
711 --PredSU->WeakSuccsLeft; 0
712 if (PredEdge->isCluster()) 0
713 NextClusterPred = PredSU; 0
714 return; 0
715 } ----
716 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
717 if (PredSU->NumSuccsLeft == 0) { 0
718 dbgs() << "*** Scheduling failed! ***\n"; 0
719 dumpNode(*PredSU); 0
720 dbgs() << " has been released too many times!\n"; 0
721 llvm_unreachable(nullptr); 0
722 } ----
723 #endif ----
724 // SU->BotReadyCycle was set to CurrCycle when it was scheduled. However, ----
725 // CurrCycle may have advanced since then. ----
726 if (PredSU->BotReadyCycle < SU->BotReadyCycle + PredEdge->getLatency()) 0
727 PredSU->BotReadyCycle = SU->BotReadyCycle + PredEdge->getLatency(); 0
728 ----
729 --PredSU->NumSuccsLeft; 0
730 if (PredSU->NumSuccsLeft == 0 && PredSU != &EntrySU) 0
731 SchedImpl->releaseBottomNode(PredSU); 0
732 } ----
733 ----
734 /// releasePredecessors - Call releasePred on each of SU's predecessors. ----
735 void ScheduleDAGMI::releasePredecessors(SUnit *SU) { 0
736 for (SDep &Pred : SU->Preds) 0
737 releasePred(SU, &Pred); 0
738 } 0
739 ----
740 void ScheduleDAGMI::startBlock(MachineBasicBlock *bb) { 0
741 ScheduleDAGInstrs::startBlock(bb); 0
742 SchedImpl->enterMBB(bb); 0
743 } 0
744 ----
745 void ScheduleDAGMI::finishBlock() { 0
746 SchedImpl->leaveMBB(); 0
747 ScheduleDAGInstrs::finishBlock(); 0
748 } 0
749 ----
750 /// enterRegion - Called back from MachineScheduler::runOnMachineFunction after ----
751 /// crossing a scheduling boundary. [begin, end) includes all instructions in ----
752 /// the region, including the boundary itself and single-instruction regions ----
753 /// that don't get scheduled. ----
754 void ScheduleDAGMI::enterRegion(MachineBasicBlock *bb, 0
755 MachineBasicBlock::iterator begin, ----
756 MachineBasicBlock::iterator end, ----
757 unsigned regioninstrs) ----
758 { ----
759 ScheduleDAGInstrs::enterRegion(bb, begin, end, regioninstrs); 0
760 ----
761 SchedImpl->initPolicy(begin, end, regioninstrs); 0
762 } 0
763 ----
764 /// This is normally called from the main scheduler loop but may also be invoked ----
765 /// by the scheduling strategy to perform additional code motion. ----
766 void ScheduleDAGMI::moveInstruction( 0
767 MachineInstr *MI, MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertPos) { ----
768 // Advance RegionBegin if the first instruction moves down. ----
769 if (&*RegionBegin == MI) 0
770 ++RegionBegin; 0
771 ----
772 // Update the instruction stream. ----
773 BB->splice(InsertPos, BB, MI); 0
774 ----
775 // Update LiveIntervals ----
776 if (LIS) 0
777 LIS->handleMove(*MI, /*UpdateFlags=*/true); 0
778 ----
779 // Recede RegionBegin if an instruction moves above the first. ----
780 if (RegionBegin == InsertPos) 0
781 RegionBegin = MI; 0
782 } 0
783 ----
784 bool ScheduleDAGMI::checkSchedLimit() { 0
785 #if LLVM_ENABLE_ABI_BREAKING_CHECKS && !defined(NDEBUG) ----
786 if (NumInstrsScheduled == MISchedCutoff && MISchedCutoff != ~0U) { 0
787 CurrentTop = CurrentBottom; 0
788 return false; 0
789 } ----
790 ++NumInstrsScheduled; 0
791 #endif ----
792 return true; 0
793 } ----
794 ----
795 /// Per-region scheduling driver, called back from ----
796 /// MachineScheduler::runOnMachineFunction. This is a simplified driver that ----
797 /// does not consider liveness or register pressure. It is useful for PostRA ----
798 /// scheduling and potentially other custom schedulers. ----
799 void ScheduleDAGMI::schedule() { 0
800 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ScheduleDAGMI::schedule starting\n"); 0
801 LLVM_DEBUG(SchedImpl->dumpPolicy()); 0
802 ----
803 // Build the DAG. ----
804 buildSchedGraph(AA); 0
805 ----
806 postProcessDAG(); 0
807 ----
808 SmallVector TopRoots, BotRoots; 0
809 findRootsAndBiasEdges(TopRoots, BotRoots); 0
810 ----
811 LLVM_DEBUG(dump()); 0
812 if (PrintDAGs) dump(); 0
813 if (ViewMISchedDAGs) viewGraph(); 0
814 ----
815 // Initialize the strategy before modifying the DAG. ----
816 // This may initialize a DFSResult to be used for queue priority. ----
817 SchedImpl->initialize(this); 0
818 ----
819 // Initialize ready queues now that the DAG and priority data are finalized. ----
820 initQueues(TopRoots, BotRoots); 0
821 ----
822 bool IsTopNode = false; 0
823 while (true) { ----
824 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "** ScheduleDAGMI::schedule picking next node\n"); 0
825 SUnit *SU = SchedImpl->pickNode(IsTopNode); 0
826 if (!SU) break; 0
827 ----
828 assert(!SU->isScheduled && "Node already scheduled"); 0
829 if (!checkSchedLimit()) 0
830 break; 0
831 ----
832 MachineInstr *MI = SU->getInstr(); 0
833 if (IsTopNode) { 0
834 assert(SU->isTopReady() && "node still has unscheduled dependencies"); 0
835 if (&*CurrentTop == MI) 0
836 CurrentTop = nextIfDebug(++CurrentTop, CurrentBottom); 0
837 else ----
838 moveInstruction(MI, CurrentTop); 0
839 } else { ----
840 assert(SU->isBottomReady() && "node still has unscheduled dependencies"); 0
841 MachineBasicBlock::iterator priorII = ----
842 priorNonDebug(CurrentBottom, CurrentTop); 0
843 if (&*priorII == MI) 0
844 CurrentBottom = priorII; 0
845 else { ----
846 if (&*CurrentTop == MI) 0
847 CurrentTop = nextIfDebug(++CurrentTop, priorII); 0
848 moveInstruction(MI, CurrentBottom); 0
849 CurrentBottom = MI; 0
850 } ----
851 } ----
852 // Notify the scheduling strategy before updating the DAG. ----
853 // This sets the scheduled node's ReadyCycle to CurrCycle. When updateQueues ----
854 // runs, it can then use the accurate ReadyCycle time to determine whether ----
855 // newly released nodes can move to the readyQ. ----
856 SchedImpl->schedNode(SU, IsTopNode); 0
857 ----
858 updateQueues(SU, IsTopNode); 0
859 } 0
860 assert(CurrentTop == CurrentBottom && "Nonempty unscheduled zone."); 0
861 ----
862 placeDebugValues(); 0
863 ----
864 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
865 dbgs() << "*** Final schedule for " ----
866 << printMBBReference(*begin()->getParent()) << " ***\n"; ----
867 dumpSchedule(); ----
868 dbgs() << '\n'; ----
869 }); ----
870 } 0
871 ----
872 /// Apply each ScheduleDAGMutation step in order. ----
873 void ScheduleDAGMI::postProcessDAG() { 0
874 for (auto &m : Mutations) 0
875 m->apply(this); 0
876 } 0
877 ----
878 void ScheduleDAGMI:: 0
879 findRootsAndBiasEdges(SmallVectorImpl &TopRoots, ----
880 SmallVectorImpl &BotRoots) { ----
881 for (SUnit &SU : SUnits) { 0
882 assert(!SU.isBoundaryNode() && "Boundary node should not be in SUnits"); 0
883 ----
884 // Order predecessors so DFSResult follows the critical path. ----
885 SU.biasCriticalPath(); 0
886 ----
887 // A SUnit is ready to top schedule if it has no predecessors. ----
888 if (!SU.NumPredsLeft) 0
889 TopRoots.push_back(&SU); 0
890 // A SUnit is ready to bottom schedule if it has no successors. ----
891 if (!SU.NumSuccsLeft) 0
892 BotRoots.push_back(&SU); 0
893 } ----
894 ExitSU.biasCriticalPath(); 0
895 } 0
896 ----
897 /// Identify DAG roots and setup scheduler queues. ----
898 void ScheduleDAGMI::initQueues(ArrayRef TopRoots, 0
899 ArrayRef BotRoots) { ----
900 NextClusterSucc = nullptr; 0
901 NextClusterPred = nullptr; 0
902 ----
903 // Release all DAG roots for scheduling, not including EntrySU/ExitSU. ----
904 // ----
905 // Nodes with unreleased weak edges can still be roots. ----
906 // Release top roots in forward order. ----
907 for (SUnit *SU : TopRoots) 0
908 SchedImpl->releaseTopNode(SU); 0
909 ----
910 // Release bottom roots in reverse order so the higher priority nodes appear ----
911 // first. This is more natural and slightly more efficient. ----
912 for (SmallVectorImpl::const_reverse_iterator 0
913 I = BotRoots.rbegin(), E = BotRoots.rend(); I != E; ++I) { 0
914 SchedImpl->releaseBottomNode(*I); 0
915 } ----
916 ----
917 releaseSuccessors(&EntrySU); 0
918 releasePredecessors(&ExitSU); 0
919 ----
920 SchedImpl->registerRoots(); 0
921 ----
922 // Advance past initial DebugValues. ----
923 CurrentTop = nextIfDebug(RegionBegin, RegionEnd); 0
924 CurrentBottom = RegionEnd; 0
925 } 0
926 ----
927 /// Update scheduler queues after scheduling an instruction. ----
928 void ScheduleDAGMI::updateQueues(SUnit *SU, bool IsTopNode) { 0
929 // Release dependent instructions for scheduling. ----
930 if (IsTopNode) 0
931 releaseSuccessors(SU); 0
932 else ----
933 releasePredecessors(SU); 0
934 ----
935 SU->isScheduled = true; 0
936 } 0
937 ----
938 /// Reinsert any remaining debug_values, just like the PostRA scheduler. ----
939 void ScheduleDAGMI::placeDebugValues() { 0
940 // If first instruction was a DBG_VALUE then put it back. ----
941 if (FirstDbgValue) { 0
942 BB->splice(RegionBegin, BB, FirstDbgValue); 0
943 RegionBegin = FirstDbgValue; 0
944 } ----
945 ----
946 for (std::vector>::iterator 0
947 DI = DbgValues.end(), DE = DbgValues.begin(); DI != DE; --DI) { 0
948 std::pair P = *std::prev(DI); 0
949 MachineInstr *DbgValue = P.first; 0
950 MachineBasicBlock::iterator OrigPrevMI = P.second; 0
951 if (&*RegionBegin == DbgValue) 0
952 ++RegionBegin; 0
953 BB->splice(std::next(OrigPrevMI), BB, DbgValue); 0
954 if (RegionEnd != BB->end() && OrigPrevMI == &*RegionEnd) 0
955 RegionEnd = DbgValue; 0
956 } ----
957 } 0
958 ----
959 #if !defined(NDEBUG) || defined(LLVM_ENABLE_DUMP) ----
960 static const char *scheduleTableLegend = " i: issue\n x: resource booked"; ----
961 ----
962 LLVM_DUMP_METHOD void ScheduleDAGMI::dumpScheduleTraceTopDown() const { 0
963 // Bail off when there is no schedule model to query. ----
964 if (!SchedModel.hasInstrSchedModel()) 0
965 return; 0
966 ----
967 // Nothing to show if there is no or just one instruction. ----
968 if (BB->size() < 2) 0
969 return; 0
970 ----
971 dbgs() << " * Schedule table (TopDown):\n"; 0
972 dbgs() << scheduleTableLegend << "\n"; 0
973 const unsigned FirstCycle = getSUnit(&*(std::begin(*this)))->TopReadyCycle; 0
974 unsigned LastCycle = getSUnit(&*(std::prev(std::end(*this))))->TopReadyCycle; 0
975 for (MachineInstr &MI : *this) { 0
976 SUnit *SU = getSUnit(&MI); 0
977 if (!SU) 0
978 continue; 0
979 const MCSchedClassDesc *SC = getSchedClass(SU); 0
980 for (TargetSchedModel::ProcResIter PI = SchedModel.getWriteProcResBegin(SC), 0
981 PE = SchedModel.getWriteProcResEnd(SC); 0
982 PI != PE; ++PI) { 0
983 if (SU->TopReadyCycle + PI->Cycles - 1 > LastCycle) 0
984 LastCycle = SU->TopReadyCycle + PI->Cycles - 1; 0
985 } ----
986 } ----
987 // Print the header with the cycles ----
988 dbgs() << llvm::left_justify("Cycle", HeaderColWidth); 0
989 for (unsigned C = FirstCycle; C <= LastCycle; ++C) 0
990 dbgs() << llvm::left_justify("| " + std::to_string(C), ColWidth); 0
991 dbgs() << "|\n"; 0
992 ----
993 for (MachineInstr &MI : *this) { 0
994 SUnit *SU = getSUnit(&MI); 0
995 if (!SU) { 0
996 dbgs() << "Missing SUnit\n"; 0
997 continue; 0
998 } ----
999 std::string NodeName("SU("); 0
1000 NodeName += std::to_string(SU->NodeNum) + ")"; 0
1001 dbgs() << llvm::left_justify(NodeName, HeaderColWidth); 0
1002 unsigned C = FirstCycle; 0
1003 for (; C <= LastCycle; ++C) { 0
1004 if (C == SU->TopReadyCycle) 0
1005 dbgs() << llvm::left_justify("| i", ColWidth); 0
1006 else ----
1007 dbgs() << llvm::left_justify("|", ColWidth); 0
1008 } ----
1009 dbgs() << "|\n"; 0
1010 const MCSchedClassDesc *SC = getSchedClass(SU); 0
1011 ----
1012 SmallVector ResourcesIt( ----
1013 make_range(SchedModel.getWriteProcResBegin(SC), 0
1014 SchedModel.getWriteProcResEnd(SC))); 0
1015 ----
1016 if (MISchedSortResourcesInTrace) 0
1017 llvm::stable_sort(ResourcesIt, 0
1018 [](const MCWriteProcResEntry &LHS, 0
1019 const MCWriteProcResEntry &RHS) -> bool { ----
1020 return LHS.StartAtCycle < RHS.StartAtCycle || 0
1021 (LHS.StartAtCycle == RHS.StartAtCycle && 0
1022 LHS.Cycles < RHS.Cycles); 0
1023 }); ----
1024 for (const MCWriteProcResEntry &PI : ResourcesIt) { 0
1025 C = FirstCycle; 0
1026 const std::string ResName = ----
1027 SchedModel.getResourceName(PI.ProcResourceIdx); 0
1028 dbgs() << llvm::right_justify(ResName + " ", HeaderColWidth); 0
1029 for (; C < SU->TopReadyCycle + PI.StartAtCycle; ++C) { 0
1030 dbgs() << llvm::left_justify("|", ColWidth); 0
1031 } ----
1032 for (unsigned I = 0, E = PI.Cycles - PI.StartAtCycle; I != E; ++I, ++C) 0
1033 dbgs() << llvm::left_justify("| x", ColWidth); 0
1034 while (C++ <= LastCycle) 0
1035 dbgs() << llvm::left_justify("|", ColWidth); 0
1036 // Place end char ----
1037 dbgs() << "| \n"; 0
1038 } 0
1039 } 0
1040 } ----
1041 ----
1042 LLVM_DUMP_METHOD void ScheduleDAGMI::dumpScheduleTraceBottomUp() const { 0
1043 // Bail off when there is no schedule model to query. ----
1044 if (!SchedModel.hasInstrSchedModel()) 0
1045 return; 0
1046 ----
1047 // Nothing to show if there is no or just one instruction. ----
1048 if (BB->size() < 2) 0
1049 return; 0
1050 ----
1051 dbgs() << " * Schedule table (BottomUp):\n"; 0
1052 dbgs() << scheduleTableLegend << "\n"; 0
1053 ----
1054 const int FirstCycle = getSUnit(&*(std::begin(*this)))->BotReadyCycle; 0
1055 int LastCycle = getSUnit(&*(std::prev(std::end(*this))))->BotReadyCycle; 0
1056 for (MachineInstr &MI : *this) { 0
1057 SUnit *SU = getSUnit(&MI); 0
1058 if (!SU) 0
1059 continue; 0
1060 const MCSchedClassDesc *SC = getSchedClass(SU); 0
1061 for (TargetSchedModel::ProcResIter PI = SchedModel.getWriteProcResBegin(SC), 0
1062 PE = SchedModel.getWriteProcResEnd(SC); 0
1063 PI != PE; ++PI) { 0
1064 if ((int)SU->BotReadyCycle - PI->Cycles + 1 < LastCycle) 0
1065 LastCycle = (int)SU->BotReadyCycle - PI->Cycles + 1; 0
1066 } ----
1067 } ----
1068 // Print the header with the cycles ----
1069 dbgs() << llvm::left_justify("Cycle", HeaderColWidth); 0
1070 for (int C = FirstCycle; C >= LastCycle; --C) 0
1071 dbgs() << llvm::left_justify("| " + std::to_string(C), ColWidth); 0
1072 dbgs() << "|\n"; 0
1073 ----
1074 for (MachineInstr &MI : *this) { 0
1075 SUnit *SU = getSUnit(&MI); 0
1076 if (!SU) { 0
1077 dbgs() << "Missing SUnit\n"; 0
1078 continue; 0
1079 } ----
1080 std::string NodeName("SU("); 0
1081 NodeName += std::to_string(SU->NodeNum) + ")"; 0
1082 dbgs() << llvm::left_justify(NodeName, HeaderColWidth); 0
1083 int C = FirstCycle; 0
1084 for (; C >= LastCycle; --C) { 0
1085 if (C == (int)SU->BotReadyCycle) 0
1086 dbgs() << llvm::left_justify("| i", ColWidth); 0
1087 else ----
1088 dbgs() << llvm::left_justify("|", ColWidth); 0
1089 } ----
1090 dbgs() << "|\n"; 0
1091 const MCSchedClassDesc *SC = getSchedClass(SU); 0
1092 SmallVector ResourcesIt( ----
1093 make_range(SchedModel.getWriteProcResBegin(SC), 0
1094 SchedModel.getWriteProcResEnd(SC))); 0
1095 ----
1096 if (MISchedSortResourcesInTrace) 0
1097 llvm::stable_sort(ResourcesIt, 0
1098 [](const MCWriteProcResEntry &LHS, 0
1099 const MCWriteProcResEntry &RHS) -> bool { ----
1100 return LHS.StartAtCycle < RHS.StartAtCycle || 0
1101 (LHS.StartAtCycle == RHS.StartAtCycle && 0
1102 LHS.Cycles < RHS.Cycles); 0
1103 }); ----
1104 for (const MCWriteProcResEntry &PI : ResourcesIt) { 0
1105 C = FirstCycle; 0
1106 const std::string ResName = ----
1107 SchedModel.getResourceName(PI.ProcResourceIdx); 0
1108 dbgs() << llvm::right_justify(ResName + " ", HeaderColWidth); 0
1109 for (; C > ((int)SU->BotReadyCycle - (int)PI.StartAtCycle); --C) { 0
1110 dbgs() << llvm::left_justify("|", ColWidth); 0
1111 } ----
1112 for (unsigned I = 0, E = PI.Cycles - PI.StartAtCycle; I != E; ++I, --C) 0
1113 dbgs() << llvm::left_justify("| x", ColWidth); 0
1114 while (C-- >= LastCycle) 0
1115 dbgs() << llvm::left_justify("|", ColWidth); 0
1116 // Place end char ----
1117 dbgs() << "| \n"; 0
1118 } 0
1119 } 0
1120 } ----
1121 #endif ----
1122 ----
1123 #if !defined(NDEBUG) || defined(LLVM_ENABLE_DUMP) ----
1124 LLVM_DUMP_METHOD void ScheduleDAGMI::dumpSchedule() const { 0
1125 if (MISchedDumpScheduleTrace) { 0
1126 if (ForceTopDown) 0
1127 dumpScheduleTraceTopDown(); 0
1128 else if (ForceBottomUp) 0
1129 dumpScheduleTraceBottomUp(); 0
1130 else { ----
1131 dbgs() << "* Schedule table (Bidirectional): not implemented\n"; 0
1132 } ----
1133 } ----
1134 ----
1135 for (MachineInstr &MI : *this) { 0
1136 if (SUnit *SU = getSUnit(&MI)) 0
1137 dumpNode(*SU); 0
1138 else ----
1139 dbgs() << "Missing SUnit\n"; 0
1140 } ----
1141 } 0
1142 #endif ----

1144 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1145 // ScheduleDAGMILive - Base class for MachineInstr scheduling with LiveIntervals ----
1146 // preservation. ----
1147 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1148 ----
1149 ScheduleDAGMILive::~ScheduleDAGMILive() { 0
1150 delete DFSResult; 0
1151 } 0
1152 ----
1153 void ScheduleDAGMILive::collectVRegUses(SUnit &SU) { 0
1154 const MachineInstr &MI = *SU.getInstr(); 0
1155 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.operands()) { 0
1156 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
1157 continue; 0
1158 if (!MO.readsReg()) 0
1159 continue; 0
1160 if (TrackLaneMasks && !MO.isUse()) 0
1161 continue; 0
1162 ----
1163 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1164 if (!Reg.isVirtual()) 0
1165 continue; 0
1166 ----
1167 // Ignore re-defs. ----
1168 if (TrackLaneMasks) { 0
1169 bool FoundDef = false; 0
1170 for (const MachineOperand &MO2 : MI.all_defs()) { 0
1171 if (MO2.getReg() == Reg && !MO2.isDead()) { 0
1172 FoundDef = true; 0
1173 break; 0
1174 } ----
1175 } ----
1176 if (FoundDef) 0
1177 continue; 0
1178 } ----
1179 ----
1180 // Record this local VReg use. ----
1181 VReg2SUnitMultiMap::iterator UI = VRegUses.find(Reg); 0
1182 for (; UI != VRegUses.end(); ++UI) { 0
1183 if (UI->SU == &SU) 0
1184 break; 0
1185 } ----
1186 if (UI == VRegUses.end()) 0
1187 VRegUses.insert(VReg2SUnit(Reg, LaneBitmask::getNone(), &SU)); 0
1188 } ----
1189 } 0
1190 ----
1191 /// enterRegion - Called back from MachineScheduler::runOnMachineFunction after ----
1192 /// crossing a scheduling boundary. [begin, end) includes all instructions in ----
1193 /// the region, including the boundary itself and single-instruction regions ----
1194 /// that don't get scheduled. ----
1195 void ScheduleDAGMILive::enterRegion(MachineBasicBlock *bb, 0
1196 MachineBasicBlock::iterator begin, ----
1197 MachineBasicBlock::iterator end, ----
1198 unsigned regioninstrs) ----
1199 { ----
1200 // ScheduleDAGMI initializes SchedImpl's per-region policy. ----
1201 ScheduleDAGMI::enterRegion(bb, begin, end, regioninstrs); 0
1202 ----
1203 // For convenience remember the end of the liveness region. ----
1204 LiveRegionEnd = (RegionEnd == bb->end()) ? RegionEnd : std::next(RegionEnd); 0
1205 ----
1206 SUPressureDiffs.clear(); 0
1207 ----
1208 ShouldTrackPressure = SchedImpl->shouldTrackPressure(); 0
1209 ShouldTrackLaneMasks = SchedImpl->shouldTrackLaneMasks(); 0
1210 ----
1211 assert((!ShouldTrackLaneMasks || ShouldTrackPressure) && 0
1212 "ShouldTrackLaneMasks requires ShouldTrackPressure"); ----
1213 } 0
1214 ----
1215 // Setup the register pressure trackers for the top scheduled and bottom ----
1216 // scheduled regions. ----
1217 void ScheduleDAGMILive::initRegPressure() { 0
1218 VRegUses.clear(); 0
1219 VRegUses.setUniverse(MRI.getNumVirtRegs()); 0
1220 for (SUnit &SU : SUnits) 0
1221 collectVRegUses(SU); 0
1222 ----
1223 TopRPTracker.init(&MF, RegClassInfo, LIS, BB, RegionBegin, 0
1224 ShouldTrackLaneMasks, false); 0
1225 BotRPTracker.init(&MF, RegClassInfo, LIS, BB, LiveRegionEnd, 0
1226 ShouldTrackLaneMasks, false); 0
1227 ----
1228 // Close the RPTracker to finalize live ins. ----
1229 RPTracker.closeRegion(); 0
1230 ----
1231 LLVM_DEBUG(RPTracker.dump()); 0
1232 ----
1233 // Initialize the live ins and live outs. ----
1234 TopRPTracker.addLiveRegs(RPTracker.getPressure().LiveInRegs); 0
1235 BotRPTracker.addLiveRegs(RPTracker.getPressure().LiveOutRegs); 0
1236 ----
1237 // Close one end of the tracker so we can call ----
1238 // getMaxUpward/DownwardPressureDelta before advancing across any ----
1239 // instructions. This converts currently live regs into live ins/outs. ----
1240 TopRPTracker.closeTop(); 0
1241 BotRPTracker.closeBottom(); 0
1242 ----
1243 BotRPTracker.initLiveThru(RPTracker); 0
1244 if (!BotRPTracker.getLiveThru().empty()) { 0
1245 TopRPTracker.initLiveThru(BotRPTracker.getLiveThru()); 0
1246 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Live Thru: "; 0
1247 dumpRegSetPressure(BotRPTracker.getLiveThru(), TRI)); ----
1248 }; ----
1249 ----
1250 // For each live out vreg reduce the pressure change associated with other ----
1251 // uses of the same vreg below the live-out reaching def. ----
1252 updatePressureDiffs(RPTracker.getPressure().LiveOutRegs); 0
1253 ----
1254 // Account for liveness generated by the region boundary. ----
1255 if (LiveRegionEnd != RegionEnd) { 0
1256 SmallVector LiveUses; 0
1257 BotRPTracker.recede(&LiveUses); 0
1258 updatePressureDiffs(LiveUses); 0
1259 } 0
1260 ----
1261 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Top Pressure:\n"; 0
1262 dumpRegSetPressure(TopRPTracker.getRegSetPressureAtPos(), TRI); ----
1263 dbgs() << "Bottom Pressure:\n"; ----
1264 dumpRegSetPressure(BotRPTracker.getRegSetPressureAtPos(), TRI);); ----
1265 ----
1266 assert((BotRPTracker.getPos() == RegionEnd || 0
1267 (RegionEnd->isDebugInstr() && ----
1268 BotRPTracker.getPos() == priorNonDebug(RegionEnd, RegionBegin))) && ----
1269 "Can't find the region bottom"); ----
1270 ----
1271 // Cache the list of excess pressure sets in this region. This will also track ----
1272 // the max pressure in the scheduled code for these sets. ----
1273 RegionCriticalPSets.clear(); 0
1274 const std::vector &RegionPressure = ----
1275 RPTracker.getPressure().MaxSetPressure; 0
1276 for (unsigned i = 0, e = RegionPressure.size(); i < e; ++i) { 0
1277 unsigned Limit = RegClassInfo->getRegPressureSetLimit(i); 0
1278 if (RegionPressure[i] > Limit) { 0
1279 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << TRI->getRegPressureSetName(i) << " Limit " << Limit 0
1280 << " Actual " << RegionPressure[i] << "\n"); ----
1281 RegionCriticalPSets.push_back(PressureChange(i)); 0
1282 } ----
1283 } ----
1284 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Excess PSets: "; 0
1285 for (const PressureChange &RCPS ----
1286 : RegionCriticalPSets) dbgs() ----
1287 << TRI->getRegPressureSetName(RCPS.getPSet()) << " "; ----
1288 dbgs() << "\n"); ----
1289 } 0
1290 ----
1291 void ScheduleDAGMILive:: 0
1292 updateScheduledPressure(const SUnit *SU, ----
1293 const std::vector &NewMaxPressure) { ----
1294 const PressureDiff &PDiff = getPressureDiff(SU); 0
1295 unsigned CritIdx = 0, CritEnd = RegionCriticalPSets.size(); 0
1296 for (const PressureChange &PC : PDiff) { 0
1297 if (!PC.isValid()) 0
1298 break; 0
1299 unsigned ID = PC.getPSet(); 0
1300 while (CritIdx != CritEnd && RegionCriticalPSets[CritIdx].getPSet() < ID) 0
1301 ++CritIdx; 0
1302 if (CritIdx != CritEnd && RegionCriticalPSets[CritIdx].getPSet() == ID) { 0
1303 if ((int)NewMaxPressure[ID] > RegionCriticalPSets[CritIdx].getUnitInc() 0
1304 && NewMaxPressure[ID] <= (unsigned)std::numeric_limits::max()) 0
1305 RegionCriticalPSets[CritIdx].setUnitInc(NewMaxPressure[ID]); 0
1306 } ----
1307 unsigned Limit = RegClassInfo->getRegPressureSetLimit(ID); 0
1308 if (NewMaxPressure[ID] >= Limit - 2) { 0
1309 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " " << TRI->getRegPressureSetName(ID) << ": " 0
1310 << NewMaxPressure[ID] ----
1311 << ((NewMaxPressure[ID] > Limit) ? " > " : " <= ") ----
1312 << Limit << "(+ " << BotRPTracker.getLiveThru()[ID] ----
1313 << " livethru)\n"); ----
1314 } ----
1315 } ----
1316 } 0
1317 ----
1318 /// Update the PressureDiff array for liveness after scheduling this ----
1319 /// instruction. ----
1320 void ScheduleDAGMILive::updatePressureDiffs( 0
1321 ArrayRef LiveUses) { ----
1322 for (const RegisterMaskPair &P : LiveUses) { 0
1323 Register Reg = P.RegUnit; 0
1324 /// FIXME: Currently assuming single-use physregs. ----
1325 if (!Reg.isVirtual()) 0
1326 continue; 0
1327 ----
1328 if (ShouldTrackLaneMasks) { 0
1329 // If the register has just become live then other uses won't change ----
1330 // this fact anymore => decrement pressure. ----
1331 // If the register has just become dead then other uses make it come ----
1332 // back to life => increment pressure. ----
1333 bool Decrement = P.LaneMask.any(); 0
1334 ----
1335 for (const VReg2SUnit &V2SU 0
1336 : make_range(VRegUses.find(Reg), VRegUses.end())) { 0
1337 SUnit &SU = *V2SU.SU; 0
1338 if (SU.isScheduled || &SU == &ExitSU) 0
1339 continue; 0
1340 ----
1341 PressureDiff &PDiff = getPressureDiff(&SU); 0
1342 PDiff.addPressureChange(Reg, Decrement, &MRI); 0
1343 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " UpdateRegP: SU(" << SU.NodeNum << ") " 0
1344 << printReg(Reg, TRI) << ':' ----
1345 << PrintLaneMask(P.LaneMask) << ' ' << *SU.getInstr(); ----
1346 dbgs() << " to "; PDiff.dump(*TRI);); ----
1347 } ----
1348 } else { ----
1349 assert(P.LaneMask.any()); 0
1350 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " LiveReg: " << printVRegOrUnit(Reg, TRI) << "\n"); 0
1351 // This may be called before CurrentBottom has been initialized. However, ----
1352 // BotRPTracker must have a valid position. We want the value live into the ----
1353 // instruction or live out of the block, so ask for the previous ----
1354 // instruction's live-out. ----
1355 const LiveInterval &LI = LIS->getInterval(Reg); 0
1356 VNInfo *VNI; ----
1357 MachineBasicBlock::const_iterator I = ----
1358 nextIfDebug(BotRPTracker.getPos(), BB->end()); 0
1359 if (I == BB->end()) 0
1360 VNI = LI.getVNInfoBefore(LIS->getMBBEndIdx(BB)); 0
1361 else { ----
1362 LiveQueryResult LRQ = LI.Query(LIS->getInstructionIndex(*I)); 0
1363 VNI = LRQ.valueIn(); 0
1364 } ----
1365 // RegisterPressureTracker guarantees that readsReg is true for LiveUses. ----
1366 assert(VNI && "No live value at use."); 0
1367 for (const VReg2SUnit &V2SU 0
1368 : make_range(VRegUses.find(Reg), VRegUses.end())) { 0
1369 SUnit *SU = V2SU.SU; 0
1370 // If this use comes before the reaching def, it cannot be a last use, ----
1371 // so decrease its pressure change. ----
1372 if (!SU->isScheduled && SU != &ExitSU) { 0
1373 LiveQueryResult LRQ = ----
1374 LI.Query(LIS->getInstructionIndex(*SU->getInstr())); 0
1375 if (LRQ.valueIn() == VNI) { 0
1376 PressureDiff &PDiff = getPressureDiff(SU); 0
1377 PDiff.addPressureChange(Reg, true, &MRI); 0
1378 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " UpdateRegP: SU(" << SU->NodeNum << ") " 0
1379 << *SU->getInstr(); ----
1380 dbgs() << " to "; PDiff.dump(*TRI);); ----
1381 } ----
1382 } ----
1383 } ----
1384 } ----
1385 } ----
1386 } 0
1387 ----
1388 void ScheduleDAGMILive::dump() const { 0
1389 #if !defined(NDEBUG) || defined(LLVM_ENABLE_DUMP) ----
1390 if (EntrySU.getInstr() != nullptr) 0
1391 dumpNodeAll(EntrySU); 0
1392 for (const SUnit &SU : SUnits) { 0
1393 dumpNodeAll(SU); 0
1394 if (ShouldTrackPressure) { 0
1395 dbgs() << " Pressure Diff : "; 0
1396 getPressureDiff(&SU).dump(*TRI); 0
1397 } ----
1398 dbgs() << " Single Issue : "; 0
1399 if (SchedModel.mustBeginGroup(SU.getInstr()) && 0
1400 SchedModel.mustEndGroup(SU.getInstr())) 0
1401 dbgs() << "true;"; 0
1402 else ----
1403 dbgs() << "false;"; 0
1404 dbgs() << '\n'; 0
1405 } ----
1406 if (ExitSU.getInstr() != nullptr) 0
1407 dumpNodeAll(ExitSU); 0
1408 #endif ----
1409 } 0
1410 ----
1411 /// schedule - Called back from MachineScheduler::runOnMachineFunction ----
1412 /// after setting up the current scheduling region. [RegionBegin, RegionEnd) ----
1413 /// only includes instructions that have DAG nodes, not scheduling boundaries. ----
1414 /// ----
1415 /// This is a skeletal driver, with all the functionality pushed into helpers, ----
1416 /// so that it can be easily extended by experimental schedulers. Generally, ----
1417 /// implementing MachineSchedStrategy should be sufficient to implement a new ----
1418 /// scheduling algorithm. However, if a scheduler further subclasses ----
1419 /// ScheduleDAGMILive then it will want to override this virtual method in order ----
1420 /// to update any specialized state. ----
1421 void ScheduleDAGMILive::schedule() { 0
1422 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ScheduleDAGMILive::schedule starting\n"); 0
1423 LLVM_DEBUG(SchedImpl->dumpPolicy()); 0
1424 buildDAGWithRegPressure(); 0
1425 ----
1426 postProcessDAG(); 0
1427 ----
1428 SmallVector TopRoots, BotRoots; 0
1429 findRootsAndBiasEdges(TopRoots, BotRoots); 0
1430 ----
1431 // Initialize the strategy before modifying the DAG. ----
1432 // This may initialize a DFSResult to be used for queue priority. ----
1433 SchedImpl->initialize(this); 0
1434 ----
1435 LLVM_DEBUG(dump()); 0
1436 if (PrintDAGs) dump(); 0
1437 if (ViewMISchedDAGs) viewGraph(); 0
1438 ----
1439 // Initialize ready queues now that the DAG and priority data are finalized. ----
1440 initQueues(TopRoots, BotRoots); 0
1441 ----
1442 bool IsTopNode = false; 0
1443 while (true) { ----
1444 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "** ScheduleDAGMILive::schedule picking next node\n"); 0
1445 SUnit *SU = SchedImpl->pickNode(IsTopNode); 0
1446 if (!SU) break; 0
1447 ----
1448 assert(!SU->isScheduled && "Node already scheduled"); 0
1449 if (!checkSchedLimit()) 0
1450 break; 0
1451 ----
1452 scheduleMI(SU, IsTopNode); 0
1453 ----
1454 if (DFSResult) { 0
1455 unsigned SubtreeID = DFSResult->getSubtreeID(SU); 0
1456 if (!ScheduledTrees.test(SubtreeID)) { 0
1457 ScheduledTrees.set(SubtreeID); 0
1458 DFSResult->scheduleTree(SubtreeID); 0
1459 SchedImpl->scheduleTree(SubtreeID); 0
1460 } ----
1461 } ----
1462 ----
1463 // Notify the scheduling strategy after updating the DAG. ----
1464 SchedImpl->schedNode(SU, IsTopNode); 0
1465 ----
1466 updateQueues(SU, IsTopNode); 0
1467 } 0
1468 assert(CurrentTop == CurrentBottom && "Nonempty unscheduled zone."); 0
1469 ----
1470 placeDebugValues(); 0
1471 ----
1472 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
1473 dbgs() << "*** Final schedule for " ----
1474 << printMBBReference(*begin()->getParent()) << " ***\n"; ----
1475 dumpSchedule(); ----
1476 dbgs() << '\n'; ----
1477 }); ----
1478 } 0
1479 ----
1480 /// Build the DAG and setup three register pressure trackers. ----
1481 void ScheduleDAGMILive::buildDAGWithRegPressure() { 0
1482 if (!ShouldTrackPressure) { 0
1483 RPTracker.reset(); 0
1484 RegionCriticalPSets.clear(); 0
1485 buildSchedGraph(AA); 0
1486 return; 0
1487 } ----
1488 ----
1489 // Initialize the register pressure tracker used by buildSchedGraph. ----
1490 RPTracker.init(&MF, RegClassInfo, LIS, BB, LiveRegionEnd, 0
1491 ShouldTrackLaneMasks, /*TrackUntiedDefs=*/true); 0
1492 ----
1493 // Account for liveness generate by the region boundary. ----
1494 if (LiveRegionEnd != RegionEnd) 0
1495 RPTracker.recede(); 0
1496 ----
1497 // Build the DAG, and compute current register pressure. ----
1498 buildSchedGraph(AA, &RPTracker, &SUPressureDiffs, LIS, ShouldTrackLaneMasks); 0
1499 ----
1500 // Initialize top/bottom trackers after computing region pressure. ----
1501 initRegPressure(); 0
1502 } ----
1503 ----
1504 void ScheduleDAGMILive::computeDFSResult() { 0
1505 if (!DFSResult) 0
1506 DFSResult = new SchedDFSResult(/*BottomU*/true, MinSubtreeSize); 0
1507 DFSResult->clear(); 0
1508 ScheduledTrees.clear(); 0
1509 DFSResult->resize(SUnits.size()); 0
1510 DFSResult->compute(SUnits); 0
1511 ScheduledTrees.resize(DFSResult->getNumSubtrees()); 0
1512 } 0
1513 ----
1514 /// Compute the max cyclic critical path through the DAG. The scheduling DAG ----
1515 /// only provides the critical path for single block loops. To handle loops that ----
1516 /// span blocks, we could use the vreg path latencies provided by ----
1517 /// MachineTraceMetrics instead. However, MachineTraceMetrics is not currently ----
1518 /// available for use in the scheduler. ----
1519 /// ----
1520 /// The cyclic path estimation identifies a def-use pair that crosses the back ----
1521 /// edge and considers the depth and height of the nodes. For example, consider ----
1522 /// the following instruction sequence where each instruction has unit latency ----
1523 /// and defines an eponymous virtual register: ----
1524 /// ----
1525 /// a->b(a,c)->c(b)->d(c)->exit ----
1526 /// ----
1527 /// The cyclic critical path is a two cycles: b->c->b ----
1528 /// The acyclic critical path is four cycles: a->b->c->d->exit ----
1529 /// LiveOutHeight = height(c) = len(c->d->exit) = 2 ----
1530 /// LiveOutDepth = depth(c) + 1 = len(a->b->c) + 1 = 3 ----
1531 /// LiveInHeight = height(b) + 1 = len(b->c->d->exit) + 1 = 4 ----
1532 /// LiveInDepth = depth(b) = len(a->b) = 1 ----
1533 /// ----
1534 /// LiveOutDepth - LiveInDepth = 3 - 1 = 2 ----
1535 /// LiveInHeight - LiveOutHeight = 4 - 2 = 2 ----
1536 /// CyclicCriticalPath = min(2, 2) = 2 ----
1537 /// ----
1538 /// This could be relevant to PostRA scheduling, but is currently implemented ----
1539 /// assuming LiveIntervals. ----
1540 unsigned ScheduleDAGMILive::computeCyclicCriticalPath() { 0
1541 // This only applies to single block loop. ----
1542 if (!BB->isSuccessor(BB)) 0
1543 return 0; 0
1544 ----
1545 unsigned MaxCyclicLatency = 0; 0
1546 // Visit each live out vreg def to find def/use pairs that cross iterations. ----
1547 for (const RegisterMaskPair &P : RPTracker.getPressure().LiveOutRegs) { 0
1548 Register Reg = P.RegUnit; 0
1549 if (!Reg.isVirtual()) 0
1550 continue; 0
1551 const LiveInterval &LI = LIS->getInterval(Reg); 0
1552 const VNInfo *DefVNI = LI.getVNInfoBefore(LIS->getMBBEndIdx(BB)); 0
1553 if (!DefVNI) 0
1554 continue; 0
1555 ----
1556 MachineInstr *DefMI = LIS->getInstructionFromIndex(DefVNI->def); 0
1557 const SUnit *DefSU = getSUnit(DefMI); 0
1558 if (!DefSU) 0
1559 continue; 0
1560 ----
1561 unsigned LiveOutHeight = DefSU->getHeight(); 0
1562 unsigned LiveOutDepth = DefSU->getDepth() + DefSU->Latency; 0
1563 // Visit all local users of the vreg def. ----
1564 for (const VReg2SUnit &V2SU 0
1565 : make_range(VRegUses.find(Reg), VRegUses.end())) { 0
1566 SUnit *SU = V2SU.SU; 0
1567 if (SU == &ExitSU) 0
1568 continue; 0
1569 ----
1570 // Only consider uses of the phi. ----
1571 LiveQueryResult LRQ = LI.Query(LIS->getInstructionIndex(*SU->getInstr())); 0
1572 if (!LRQ.valueIn()->isPHIDef()) 0
1573 continue; 0
1574 ----
1575 // Assume that a path spanning two iterations is a cycle, which could ----
1576 // overestimate in strange cases. This allows cyclic latency to be ----
1577 // estimated as the minimum slack of the vreg's depth or height. ----
1578 unsigned CyclicLatency = 0; 0
1579 if (LiveOutDepth > SU->getDepth()) 0
1580 CyclicLatency = LiveOutDepth - SU->getDepth(); 0
1581 ----
1582 unsigned LiveInHeight = SU->getHeight() + DefSU->Latency; 0
1583 if (LiveInHeight > LiveOutHeight) { 0
1584 if (LiveInHeight - LiveOutHeight < CyclicLatency) 0
1585 CyclicLatency = LiveInHeight - LiveOutHeight; 0
1586 } else ----
1587 CyclicLatency = 0; 0
1588 ----
1589 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Cyclic Path: SU(" << DefSU->NodeNum << ") -> SU(" 0
1590 << SU->NodeNum << ") = " << CyclicLatency << "c\n"); ----
1591 if (CyclicLatency > MaxCyclicLatency) 0
1592 MaxCyclicLatency = CyclicLatency; 0
1593 } ----
1594 } ----
1595 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Cyclic Critical Path: " << MaxCyclicLatency << "c\n"); 0
1596 return MaxCyclicLatency; 0
1597 } ----
1598 ----
1599 /// Release ExitSU predecessors and setup scheduler queues. Re-position ----
1600 /// the Top RP tracker in case the region beginning has changed. ----
1601 void ScheduleDAGMILive::initQueues(ArrayRef TopRoots, 0
1602 ArrayRef BotRoots) { ----
1603 ScheduleDAGMI::initQueues(TopRoots, BotRoots); 0
1604 if (ShouldTrackPressure) { 0
1605 assert(TopRPTracker.getPos() == RegionBegin && "bad initial Top tracker"); 0
1606 TopRPTracker.setPos(CurrentTop); 0
1607 } ----
1608 } 0
1609 ----
1610 /// Move an instruction and update register pressure. ----
1611 void ScheduleDAGMILive::scheduleMI(SUnit *SU, bool IsTopNode) { 0
1612 // Move the instruction to its new location in the instruction stream. ----
1613 MachineInstr *MI = SU->getInstr(); 0
1614 ----
1615 if (IsTopNode) { 0
1616 assert(SU->isTopReady() && "node still has unscheduled dependencies"); 0
1617 if (&*CurrentTop == MI) 0
1618 CurrentTop = nextIfDebug(++CurrentTop, CurrentBottom); 0
1619 else { ----
1620 moveInstruction(MI, CurrentTop); 0
1621 TopRPTracker.setPos(MI); 0
1622 } ----
1623 ----
1624 if (ShouldTrackPressure) { 0
1625 // Update top scheduled pressure. ----
1626 RegisterOperands RegOpers; 0
1627 RegOpers.collect(*MI, *TRI, MRI, ShouldTrackLaneMasks, false); 0
1628 if (ShouldTrackLaneMasks) { 0
1629 // Adjust liveness and add missing dead+read-undef flags. ----
1630 SlotIndex SlotIdx = LIS->getInstructionIndex(*MI).getRegSlot(); 0
1631 RegOpers.adjustLaneLiveness(*LIS, MRI, SlotIdx, MI); 0
1632 } else { ----
1633 // Adjust for missing dead-def flags. ----
1634 RegOpers.detectDeadDefs(*MI, *LIS); 0
1635 } ----
1636 ----
1637 TopRPTracker.advance(RegOpers); 0
1638 assert(TopRPTracker.getPos() == CurrentTop && "out of sync"); 0
1639 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Top Pressure:\n"; dumpRegSetPressure( 0
1640 TopRPTracker.getRegSetPressureAtPos(), TRI);); ----
1641 ----
1642 updateScheduledPressure(SU, TopRPTracker.getPressure().MaxSetPressure); 0
1643 } 0
1644 } else { ----
1645 assert(SU->isBottomReady() && "node still has unscheduled dependencies"); 0
1646 MachineBasicBlock::iterator priorII = ----
1647 priorNonDebug(CurrentBottom, CurrentTop); 0
1648 if (&*priorII == MI) 0
1649 CurrentBottom = priorII; 0
1650 else { ----
1651 if (&*CurrentTop == MI) { 0
1652 CurrentTop = nextIfDebug(++CurrentTop, priorII); 0
1653 TopRPTracker.setPos(CurrentTop); 0
1654 } ----
1655 moveInstruction(MI, CurrentBottom); 0
1656 CurrentBottom = MI; 0
1657 BotRPTracker.setPos(CurrentBottom); 0
1658 } ----
1659 if (ShouldTrackPressure) { 0
1660 RegisterOperands RegOpers; 0
1661 RegOpers.collect(*MI, *TRI, MRI, ShouldTrackLaneMasks, false); 0
1662 if (ShouldTrackLaneMasks) { 0
1663 // Adjust liveness and add missing dead+read-undef flags. ----
1664 SlotIndex SlotIdx = LIS->getInstructionIndex(*MI).getRegSlot(); 0
1665 RegOpers.adjustLaneLiveness(*LIS, MRI, SlotIdx, MI); 0
1666 } else { ----
1667 // Adjust for missing dead-def flags. ----
1668 RegOpers.detectDeadDefs(*MI, *LIS); 0
1669 } ----
1670 ----
1671 if (BotRPTracker.getPos() != CurrentBottom) 0
1672 BotRPTracker.recedeSkipDebugValues(); 0
1673 SmallVector LiveUses; 0
1674 BotRPTracker.recede(RegOpers, &LiveUses); 0
1675 assert(BotRPTracker.getPos() == CurrentBottom && "out of sync"); 0
1676 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Bottom Pressure:\n"; dumpRegSetPressure( 0
1677 BotRPTracker.getRegSetPressureAtPos(), TRI);); ----
1678 ----
1679 updateScheduledPressure(SU, BotRPTracker.getPressure().MaxSetPressure); 0
1680 updatePressureDiffs(LiveUses); 0
1681 } 0
1682 } ----
1683 } 0
1684 ----
1685 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1686 // BaseMemOpClusterMutation - DAG post-processing to cluster loads or stores. ----
1687 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1688 ----
1689 namespace { ----
1690 ----
1691 /// Post-process the DAG to create cluster edges between neighboring ----
1692 /// loads or between neighboring stores. ----
1693 class BaseMemOpClusterMutation : public ScheduleDAGMutation { ----
1694 struct MemOpInfo { ----
1695 SUnit *SU; ----
1696 SmallVector BaseOps; ----
1697 int64_t Offset; ----
1698 unsigned Width; ----
1699 ----
1700 MemOpInfo(SUnit *SU, ArrayRef BaseOps, 0
1701 int64_t Offset, unsigned Width) ----
1702 : SU(SU), BaseOps(BaseOps.begin(), BaseOps.end()), Offset(Offset), 0
1703 Width(Width) {} 0
1704 ----
1705 static bool Compare(const MachineOperand *const &A, 0
1706 const MachineOperand *const &B) { ----
1707 if (A->getType() != B->getType()) 0
1708 return A->getType() < B->getType(); 0
1709 if (A->isReg()) 0
1710 return A->getReg() < B->getReg(); 0
1711 if (A->isFI()) { 0
1712 const MachineFunction &MF = *A->getParent()->getParent()->getParent(); 0
1713 const TargetFrameLowering &TFI = *MF.getSubtarget().getFrameLowering(); 0
1714 bool StackGrowsDown = TFI.getStackGrowthDirection() == 0
1715 TargetFrameLowering::StackGrowsDown; 0
1716 return StackGrowsDown ? A->getIndex() > B->getIndex() 0
1717 : A->getIndex() < B->getIndex(); 0
1718 } ----
1719 ----
1720 llvm_unreachable("MemOpClusterMutation only supports register or frame " 0
1721 "index bases."); ----
1722 } ----
1723 ----
1724 bool operator<(const MemOpInfo &RHS) const { 0
1725 // FIXME: Don't compare everything twice. Maybe use C++20 three way ----
1726 // comparison instead when it's available. ----
1727 if (std::lexicographical_compare(BaseOps.begin(), BaseOps.end(), 0
1728 RHS.BaseOps.begin(), RHS.BaseOps.end(), ----
1729 Compare)) ----
1730 return true; 0
1731 if (std::lexicographical_compare(RHS.BaseOps.begin(), RHS.BaseOps.end(), 0
1732 BaseOps.begin(), BaseOps.end(), Compare)) ----
1733 return false; 0
1734 if (Offset != RHS.Offset) 0
1735 return Offset < RHS.Offset; 0
1736 return SU->NodeNum < RHS.SU->NodeNum; 0
1737 } ----
1738 }; ----
1739 ----
1740 const TargetInstrInfo *TII; ----
1741 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI; ----
1742 bool IsLoad; ----
1743 ----
1744 public: ----
1745 BaseMemOpClusterMutation(const TargetInstrInfo *tii, 0
1746 const TargetRegisterInfo *tri, bool IsLoad) ----
1747 : TII(tii), TRI(tri), IsLoad(IsLoad) {} 0
1748 ----
1749 void apply(ScheduleDAGInstrs *DAGInstrs) override; ----
1750 ----
1751 protected: ----
1752 void clusterNeighboringMemOps(ArrayRef MemOps, bool FastCluster, ----
1753 ScheduleDAGInstrs *DAG); ----
1754 void collectMemOpRecords(std::vector &SUnits, ----
1755 SmallVectorImpl &MemOpRecords); ----
1756 bool groupMemOps(ArrayRef MemOps, ScheduleDAGInstrs *DAG, ----
1757 DenseMap> &Groups); ----
1758 }; ----

1792 ----
1793 // Sorting all the loads/stores first, then for each load/store, checking the ----
1794 // following load/store one by one, until reach the first non-dependent one and ----
1795 // call target hook to see if they can cluster. ----
1796 // If FastCluster is enabled, we assume that, all the loads/stores have been ----
1797 // preprocessed and now, they didn't have dependencies on each other. ----
1798 void BaseMemOpClusterMutation::clusterNeighboringMemOps( 0
1799 ArrayRef MemOpRecords, bool FastCluster, ----
1800 ScheduleDAGInstrs *DAG) { ----
1801 // Keep track of the current cluster length and bytes for each SUnit. ----
1802 DenseMap> SUnit2ClusterInfo; 0
1803 ----
1804 // At this point, `MemOpRecords` array must hold atleast two mem ops. Try to ----
1805 // cluster mem ops collected within `MemOpRecords` array. ----
1806 for (unsigned Idx = 0, End = MemOpRecords.size(); Idx < (End - 1); ++Idx) { 0
1807 // Decision to cluster mem ops is taken based on target dependent logic ----
1808 auto MemOpa = MemOpRecords[Idx]; 0
1809 ----
1810 // Seek for the next load/store to do the cluster. ----
1811 unsigned NextIdx = Idx + 1; 0
1812 for (; NextIdx < End; ++NextIdx) 0
1813 // Skip if MemOpb has been clustered already or has dependency with ----
1814 // MemOpa. ----
1815 if (!SUnit2ClusterInfo.count(MemOpRecords[NextIdx].SU->NodeNum) && 0
1816 (FastCluster || 0
1817 (!DAG->IsReachable(MemOpRecords[NextIdx].SU, MemOpa.SU) && 0
1818 !DAG->IsReachable(MemOpa.SU, MemOpRecords[NextIdx].SU)))) 0
1819 break; 0
1820 if (NextIdx == End) 0
1821 continue; 0
1822 ----
1823 auto MemOpb = MemOpRecords[NextIdx]; 0
1824 unsigned ClusterLength = 2; 0
1825 unsigned CurrentClusterBytes = MemOpa.Width + MemOpb.Width; 0
1826 if (SUnit2ClusterInfo.count(MemOpa.SU->NodeNum)) { 0
1827 ClusterLength = SUnit2ClusterInfo[MemOpa.SU->NodeNum].first + 1; 0
1828 CurrentClusterBytes = 0
1829 SUnit2ClusterInfo[MemOpa.SU->NodeNum].second + MemOpb.Width; 0
1830 } ----
1831 ----
1832 if (!TII->shouldClusterMemOps(MemOpa.BaseOps, MemOpb.BaseOps, ClusterLength, 0
1833 CurrentClusterBytes)) ----
1834 continue; 0
1835 ----
1836 SUnit *SUa = MemOpa.SU; 0
1837 SUnit *SUb = MemOpb.SU; 0
1838 if (SUa->NodeNum > SUb->NodeNum) 0
1839 std::swap(SUa, SUb); 0
1840 ----
1841 // FIXME: Is this check really required? ----
1842 if (!DAG->addEdge(SUb, SDep(SUa, SDep::Cluster))) 0
1843 continue; 0
1844 ----
1845 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Cluster ld/st SU(" << SUa->NodeNum << ") - SU(" 0
1846 << SUb->NodeNum << ")\n"); ----
1847 ++NumClustered; 0
1848 ----
1849 if (IsLoad) { 0
1850 // Copy successor edges from SUa to SUb. Interleaving computation ----
1851 // dependent on SUa can prevent load combining due to register reuse. ----
1852 // Predecessor edges do not need to be copied from SUb to SUa since ----
1853 // nearby loads should have effectively the same inputs. ----
1854 for (const SDep &Succ : SUa->Succs) { 0
1855 if (Succ.getSUnit() == SUb) 0
1856 continue; 0
1857 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Copy Succ SU(" << Succ.getSUnit()->NodeNum 0
1858 << ")\n"); ----
1859 DAG->addEdge(Succ.getSUnit(), SDep(SUb, SDep::Artificial)); 0
1860 } ----
1861 } else { ----
1862 // Copy predecessor edges from SUb to SUa to avoid the SUnits that ----
1863 // SUb dependent on scheduled in-between SUb and SUa. Successor edges ----
1864 // do not need to be copied from SUa to SUb since no one will depend ----
1865 // on stores. ----
1866 // Notice that, we don't need to care about the memory dependency as ----
1867 // we won't try to cluster them if they have any memory dependency. ----
1868 for (const SDep &Pred : SUb->Preds) { 0
1869 if (Pred.getSUnit() == SUa) 0
1870 continue; 0
1871 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Copy Pred SU(" << Pred.getSUnit()->NodeNum 0
1872 << ")\n"); ----
1873 DAG->addEdge(SUa, SDep(Pred.getSUnit(), SDep::Artificial)); 0
1874 } ----
1875 } ----
1876 ----
1877 SUnit2ClusterInfo[MemOpb.SU->NodeNum] = {ClusterLength, 0
1878 CurrentClusterBytes}; 0
1879 ----
1880 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Curr cluster length: " << ClusterLength 0
1881 << ", Curr cluster bytes: " << CurrentClusterBytes ----
1882 << "\n"); ----
1883 } 0
1884 } 0
1885 ----
1886 void BaseMemOpClusterMutation::collectMemOpRecords( 0
1887 std::vector &SUnits, SmallVectorImpl &MemOpRecords) { ----
1888 for (auto &SU : SUnits) { 0
1889 if ((IsLoad && !SU.getInstr()->mayLoad()) || 0
1890 (!IsLoad && !SU.getInstr()->mayStore())) 0
1891 continue; 0
1892 ----
1893 const MachineInstr &MI = *SU.getInstr(); 0
1894 SmallVector BaseOps; 0
1895 int64_t Offset; ----
1896 bool OffsetIsScalable; ----
1897 unsigned Width; ----
1898 if (TII->getMemOperandsWithOffsetWidth(MI, BaseOps, Offset, 0
1899 OffsetIsScalable, Width, TRI)) { ----
1900 MemOpRecords.push_back(MemOpInfo(&SU, BaseOps, Offset, Width)); 0
1901 ----
1902 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Num BaseOps: " << BaseOps.size() << ", Offset: " 0
1903 << Offset << ", OffsetIsScalable: " << OffsetIsScalable ----
1904 << ", Width: " << Width << "\n"); ----
1905 } ----
1906 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
1907 for (const auto *Op : BaseOps) 0
1908 assert(Op); 0
1909 #endif ----
1910 } 0
1911 } 0
1912 ----
1913 bool BaseMemOpClusterMutation::groupMemOps( 0
1914 ArrayRef MemOps, ScheduleDAGInstrs *DAG, ----
1915 DenseMap> &Groups) { ----
1916 bool FastCluster = ----
1917 ForceFastCluster || 0
1918 MemOps.size() * DAG->SUnits.size() / 1000 > FastClusterThreshold; 0
1919 ----
1920 for (const auto &MemOp : MemOps) { 0
1921 unsigned ChainPredID = DAG->SUnits.size(); 0
1922 if (FastCluster) { 0
1923 for (const SDep &Pred : MemOp.SU->Preds) { 0
1924 // We only want to cluster the mem ops that have the same ctrl(non-data) ----
1925 // pred so that they didn't have ctrl dependency for each other. But for ----
1926 // store instrs, we can still cluster them if the pred is load instr. ----
1927 if ((Pred.isCtrl() && 0
1928 (IsLoad || 0
1929 (Pred.getSUnit() && Pred.getSUnit()->getInstr()->mayStore()))) && 0
1930 !Pred.isArtificial()) { 0
1931 ChainPredID = Pred.getSUnit()->NodeNum; 0
1932 break; 0
1933 } ----
1934 } ----
1935 } else ----
1936 ChainPredID = 0; 0
1937 ----
1938 Groups[ChainPredID].push_back(MemOp); 0
1939 } ----
1940 return FastCluster; 0
1941 } ----
1942 ----
1943 /// Callback from DAG postProcessing to create cluster edges for loads/stores. ----
1944 void BaseMemOpClusterMutation::apply(ScheduleDAGInstrs *DAG) { 0
1945 // Collect all the clusterable loads/stores ----
1946 SmallVector MemOpRecords; 0
1947 collectMemOpRecords(DAG->SUnits, MemOpRecords); 0
1948 ----
1949 if (MemOpRecords.size() < 2) 0
1950 return; 0
1951 ----
1952 // Put the loads/stores without dependency into the same group with some ----
1953 // heuristic if the DAG is too complex to avoid compiling time blow up. ----
1954 // Notice that, some fusion pair could be lost with this. ----
1955 DenseMap> Groups; 0
1956 bool FastCluster = groupMemOps(MemOpRecords, DAG, Groups); 0
1957 ----
1958 for (auto &Group : Groups) { 0
1959 // Sorting the loads/stores, so that, we can stop the cluster as early as ----
1960 // possible. ----
1961 llvm::sort(Group.second); 0
1962 ----
1963 // Trying to cluster all the neighboring loads/stores. ----
1964 clusterNeighboringMemOps(Group.second, FastCluster, DAG); 0
1965 } ----
1966 } 0
1967 ----
1968 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1969 // CopyConstrain - DAG post-processing to encourage copy elimination. ----
1970 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1971 ----
1972 namespace { ----
1973 ----
1974 /// Post-process the DAG to create weak edges from all uses of a copy to ----
1975 /// the one use that defines the copy's source vreg, most likely an induction ----
1976 /// variable increment. ----
1977 class CopyConstrain : public ScheduleDAGMutation { ----
1978 // Transient state. ----
1979 SlotIndex RegionBeginIdx; ----
1980 ----
1981 // RegionEndIdx is the slot index of the last non-debug instruction in the ----
1982 // scheduling region. So we may have RegionBeginIdx == RegionEndIdx. ----
1983 SlotIndex RegionEndIdx; ----
1984 ----
1985 public: ----
1986 CopyConstrain(const TargetInstrInfo *, const TargetRegisterInfo *) {} 0
1987 ----
1988 void apply(ScheduleDAGInstrs *DAGInstrs) override; ----
1989 ----
1990 protected: ----
1991 void constrainLocalCopy(SUnit *CopySU, ScheduleDAGMILive *DAG); ----
1992 }; ----
1993 ----
1994 } // end anonymous namespace ----
1995 ----
1996 namespace llvm { ----
1997 ----
1998 std::unique_ptr ----
1999 createCopyConstrainDAGMutation(const TargetInstrInfo *TII, 0
2000 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI) { ----
2001 return std::make_unique(TII, TRI); 0
2002 } ----
2003 ----
2004 } // end namespace llvm ----
2005 ----
2006 /// constrainLocalCopy handles two possibilities: ----
2007 /// 1) Local src: ----
2008 /// I0: = dst ----
2009 /// I1: src = ... ----
2010 /// I2: = dst ----
2011 /// I3: dst = src (copy) ----
2012 /// (create pred->succ edges I0->I1, I2->I1) ----
2013 /// ----
2014 /// 2) Local copy: ----
2015 /// I0: dst = src (copy) ----
2016 /// I1: = dst ----
2017 /// I2: src = ... ----
2018 /// I3: = dst ----
2019 /// (create pred->succ edges I1->I2, I3->I2) ----
2020 /// ----
2021 /// Although the MachineScheduler is currently constrained to single blocks, ----
2022 /// this algorithm should handle extended blocks. An EBB is a set of ----
2023 /// contiguously numbered blocks such that the previous block in the EBB is ----
2024 /// always the single predecessor. ----
2025 void CopyConstrain::constrainLocalCopy(SUnit *CopySU, ScheduleDAGMILive *DAG) { 0
2026 LiveIntervals *LIS = DAG->getLIS(); 0
2027 MachineInstr *Copy = CopySU->getInstr(); 0
2028 ----
2029 // Check for pure vreg copies. ----
2030 const MachineOperand &SrcOp = Copy->getOperand(1); 0
2031 Register SrcReg = SrcOp.getReg(); 0
2032 if (!SrcReg.isVirtual() || !SrcOp.readsReg()) 0
2033 return; 0
2034 ----
2035 const MachineOperand &DstOp = Copy->getOperand(0); 0
2036 Register DstReg = DstOp.getReg(); 0
2037 if (!DstReg.isVirtual() || DstOp.isDead()) 0
2038 return; 0
2039 ----
2040 // Check if either the dest or source is local. If it's live across a back ----
2041 // edge, it's not local. Note that if both vregs are live across the back ----
2042 // edge, we cannot successfully contrain the copy without cyclic scheduling. ----
2043 // If both the copy's source and dest are local live intervals, then we ----
2044 // should treat the dest as the global for the purpose of adding ----
2045 // constraints. This adds edges from source's other uses to the copy. ----
2046 unsigned LocalReg = SrcReg; 0
2047 unsigned GlobalReg = DstReg; 0
2048 LiveInterval *LocalLI = &LIS->getInterval(LocalReg); 0
2049 if (!LocalLI->isLocal(RegionBeginIdx, RegionEndIdx)) { 0
2050 LocalReg = DstReg; 0
2051 GlobalReg = SrcReg; 0
2052 LocalLI = &LIS->getInterval(LocalReg); 0
2053 if (!LocalLI->isLocal(RegionBeginIdx, RegionEndIdx)) 0
2054 return; 0
2055 } ----
2056 LiveInterval *GlobalLI = &LIS->getInterval(GlobalReg); 0
2057 ----
2058 // Find the global segment after the start of the local LI. ----
2059 LiveInterval::iterator GlobalSegment = GlobalLI->find(LocalLI->beginIndex()); 0
2060 // If GlobalLI does not overlap LocalLI->start, then a copy directly feeds a ----
2061 // local live range. We could create edges from other global uses to the local ----
2062 // start, but the coalescer should have already eliminated these cases, so ----
2063 // don't bother dealing with it. ----
2064 if (GlobalSegment == GlobalLI->end()) 0
2065 return; 0
2066 ----
2067 // If GlobalSegment is killed at the LocalLI->start, the call to find() ----
2068 // returned the next global segment. But if GlobalSegment overlaps with ----
2069 // LocalLI->start, then advance to the next segment. If a hole in GlobalLI ----
2070 // exists in LocalLI's vicinity, GlobalSegment will be the end of the hole. ----
2071 if (GlobalSegment->contains(LocalLI->beginIndex())) 0
2072 ++GlobalSegment; 0
2073 ----
2074 if (GlobalSegment == GlobalLI->end()) 0
2075 return; 0
2076 ----
2077 // Check if GlobalLI contains a hole in the vicinity of LocalLI. ----
2078 if (GlobalSegment != GlobalLI->begin()) { 0
2079 // Two address defs have no hole. ----
2080 if (SlotIndex::isSameInstr(std::prev(GlobalSegment)->end, 0
2081 GlobalSegment->start)) { ----
2082 return; 0
2083 } ----
2084 // If the prior global segment may be defined by the same two-address ----
2085 // instruction that also defines LocalLI, then can't make a hole here. ----
2086 if (SlotIndex::isSameInstr(std::prev(GlobalSegment)->start, 0
2087 LocalLI->beginIndex())) { ----
2088 return; 0
2089 } ----
2090 // If GlobalLI has a prior segment, it must be live into the EBB. Otherwise ----
2091 // it would be a disconnected component in the live range. ----
2092 assert(std::prev(GlobalSegment)->start < LocalLI->beginIndex() && 0
2093 "Disconnected LRG within the scheduling region."); ----
2094 } ----
2095 MachineInstr *GlobalDef = LIS->getInstructionFromIndex(GlobalSegment->start); 0
2096 if (!GlobalDef) 0
2097 return; 0
2098 ----
2099 SUnit *GlobalSU = DAG->getSUnit(GlobalDef); 0
2100 if (!GlobalSU) 0
2101 return; 0
2102 ----
2103 // GlobalDef is the bottom of the GlobalLI hole. Open the hole by ----
2104 // constraining the uses of the last local def to precede GlobalDef. ----
2105 SmallVector LocalUses; 0
2106 const VNInfo *LastLocalVN = LocalLI->getVNInfoBefore(LocalLI->endIndex()); 0
2107 MachineInstr *LastLocalDef = LIS->getInstructionFromIndex(LastLocalVN->def); 0
2108 SUnit *LastLocalSU = DAG->getSUnit(LastLocalDef); 0
2109 for (const SDep &Succ : LastLocalSU->Succs) { 0
2110 if (Succ.getKind() != SDep::Data || Succ.getReg() != LocalReg) 0
2111 continue; 0
2112 if (Succ.getSUnit() == GlobalSU) 0
2113 continue; 0
2114 if (!DAG->canAddEdge(GlobalSU, Succ.getSUnit())) 0
2115 return; 0
2116 LocalUses.push_back(Succ.getSUnit()); 0
2117 } ----
2118 // Open the top of the GlobalLI hole by constraining any earlier global uses ----
2119 // to precede the start of LocalLI. ----
2120 SmallVector GlobalUses; 0
2121 MachineInstr *FirstLocalDef = ----
2122 LIS->getInstructionFromIndex(LocalLI->beginIndex()); 0
2123 SUnit *FirstLocalSU = DAG->getSUnit(FirstLocalDef); 0
2124 for (const SDep &Pred : GlobalSU->Preds) { 0
2125 if (Pred.getKind() != SDep::Anti || Pred.getReg() != GlobalReg) 0
2126 continue; 0
2127 if (Pred.getSUnit() == FirstLocalSU) 0
2128 continue; 0
2129 if (!DAG->canAddEdge(FirstLocalSU, Pred.getSUnit())) 0
2130 return; 0
2131 GlobalUses.push_back(Pred.getSUnit()); 0
2132 } ----
2133 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Constraining copy SU(" << CopySU->NodeNum << ")\n"); 0
2134 // Add the weak edges. ----
2135 for (SUnit *LU : LocalUses) { 0
2136 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Local use SU(" << LU->NodeNum << ") -> SU(" 0
2137 << GlobalSU->NodeNum << ")\n"); ----
2138 DAG->addEdge(GlobalSU, SDep(LU, SDep::Weak)); 0
2139 } ----
2140 for (SUnit *GU : GlobalUses) { 0
2141 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Global use SU(" << GU->NodeNum << ") -> SU(" 0
2142 << FirstLocalSU->NodeNum << ")\n"); ----
2143 DAG->addEdge(FirstLocalSU, SDep(GU, SDep::Weak)); 0
2144 } ----
2145 } 0
2146 ----
2147 /// Callback from DAG postProcessing to create weak edges to encourage ----
2148 /// copy elimination. ----
2149 void CopyConstrain::apply(ScheduleDAGInstrs *DAGInstrs) { 0
2150 ScheduleDAGMI *DAG = static_cast(DAGInstrs); 0
2151 assert(DAG->hasVRegLiveness() && "Expect VRegs with LiveIntervals"); 0
2152 ----
2153 MachineBasicBlock::iterator FirstPos = nextIfDebug(DAG->begin(), DAG->end()); 0
2154 if (FirstPos == DAG->end()) 0
2155 return; 0
2156 RegionBeginIdx = DAG->getLIS()->getInstructionIndex(*FirstPos); 0
2157 RegionEndIdx = DAG->getLIS()->getInstructionIndex( 0
2158 *priorNonDebug(DAG->end(), DAG->begin())); 0
2159 ----
2160 for (SUnit &SU : DAG->SUnits) { 0
2161 if (!SU.getInstr()->isCopy()) 0
2162 continue; 0
2163 ----
2164 constrainLocalCopy(&SU, static_cast(DAG)); 0
2165 } ----
2166 } ----

2169 // MachineSchedStrategy helpers used by GenericScheduler, GenericPostScheduler ----
2170 // and possibly other custom schedulers. ----
2171 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
