2173 static const unsigned InvalidCycle = ~0U; ----
2174 ----
2175 SchedBoundary::~SchedBoundary() { delete HazardRec; } 0
2176 ----
2177 /// Given a Count of resource usage and a Latency value, return true if a ----
2178 /// SchedBoundary becomes resource limited. ----
2179 /// If we are checking after scheduling a node, we should return true when ----
2180 /// we just reach the resource limit. ----
2181 static bool checkResourceLimit(unsigned LFactor, unsigned Count, 0
2182 unsigned Latency, bool AfterSchedNode) { ----
2183 int ResCntFactor = (int)(Count - (Latency * LFactor)); 0
2184 if (AfterSchedNode) 0
2185 return ResCntFactor >= (int)LFactor; 0
2186 else ----
2187 return ResCntFactor > (int)LFactor; 0
2188 } ----
2189 ----
2190 void SchedBoundary::reset() { 0
2191 // A new HazardRec is created for each DAG and owned by SchedBoundary. ----
2192 // Destroying and reconstructing it is very expensive though. So keep ----
2193 // invalid, placeholder HazardRecs. ----
2194 if (HazardRec && HazardRec->isEnabled()) { 0
2195 delete HazardRec; 0
2196 HazardRec = nullptr; 0
2197 } ----
2198 Available.clear(); 0
2199 Pending.clear(); 0
2200 CheckPending = false; 0
2201 CurrCycle = 0; 0
2202 CurrMOps = 0; 0
2203 MinReadyCycle = std::numeric_limits::max(); 0
2204 ExpectedLatency = 0; 0
2205 DependentLatency = 0; 0
2206 RetiredMOps = 0; 0
2207 MaxExecutedResCount = 0; 0
2208 ZoneCritResIdx = 0; 0
2209 IsResourceLimited = false; 0
2210 ReservedCycles.clear(); 0
2211 ReservedResourceSegments.clear(); 0
2212 ReservedCyclesIndex.clear(); 0
2213 ResourceGroupSubUnitMasks.clear(); 0
2214 #if LLVM_ENABLE_ABI_BREAKING_CHECKS ----
2215 // Track the maximum number of stall cycles that could arise either from the ----
2216 // latency of a DAG edge or the number of cycles that a processor resource is ----
2217 // reserved (SchedBoundary::ReservedCycles). ----
2218 MaxObservedStall = 0; 0
2219 #endif ----
2220 // Reserve a zero-count for invalid CritResIdx. ----
2221 ExecutedResCounts.resize(1); 0
2222 assert(!ExecutedResCounts[0] && "nonzero count for bad resource"); 0
2223 } 0
2224 ----
2225 void SchedRemainder:: 0
2226 init(ScheduleDAGMI *DAG, const TargetSchedModel *SchedModel) { ----
2227 reset(); 0
2228 if (!SchedModel->hasInstrSchedModel()) 0
2229 return; 0
2230 RemainingCounts.resize(SchedModel->getNumProcResourceKinds()); 0
2231 for (SUnit &SU : DAG->SUnits) { 0
2232 const MCSchedClassDesc *SC = DAG->getSchedClass(&SU); 0
2233 RemIssueCount += SchedModel->getNumMicroOps(SU.getInstr(), SC) 0
2234 * SchedModel->getMicroOpFactor(); 0
2235 for (TargetSchedModel::ProcResIter 0
2236 PI = SchedModel->getWriteProcResBegin(SC), 0
2237 PE = SchedModel->getWriteProcResEnd(SC); PI != PE; ++PI) { 0
2238 unsigned PIdx = PI->ProcResourceIdx; 0
2239 unsigned Factor = SchedModel->getResourceFactor(PIdx); 0
2240 assert(PI->Cycles >= PI->StartAtCycle); 0
2241 RemainingCounts[PIdx] += (Factor * (PI->Cycles - PI->StartAtCycle)); 0
2242 } ----
2243 } ----
2244 } ----
2245 ----
2246 void SchedBoundary:: 0
2247 init(ScheduleDAGMI *dag, const TargetSchedModel *smodel, SchedRemainder *rem) { ----
2248 reset(); 0
2249 DAG = dag; 0
2250 SchedModel = smodel; 0
2251 Rem = rem; 0
2252 if (SchedModel->hasInstrSchedModel()) { 0
2253 unsigned ResourceCount = SchedModel->getNumProcResourceKinds(); 0
2254 ReservedCyclesIndex.resize(ResourceCount); 0
2255 ExecutedResCounts.resize(ResourceCount); 0
2256 ResourceGroupSubUnitMasks.resize(ResourceCount, APInt(ResourceCount, 0)); 0
2257 unsigned NumUnits = 0; 0
2258 ----
2259 for (unsigned i = 0; i < ResourceCount; ++i) { 0
2260 ReservedCyclesIndex[i] = NumUnits; 0
2261 NumUnits += SchedModel->getProcResource(i)->NumUnits; 0
2262 if (isUnbufferedGroup(i)) { 0
2263 auto SubUnits = SchedModel->getProcResource(i)->SubUnitsIdxBegin; 0
2264 for (unsigned U = 0, UE = SchedModel->getProcResource(i)->NumUnits; 0
2265 U != UE; ++U) 0
2266 ResourceGroupSubUnitMasks[i].setBit(SubUnits[U]); 0
2267 } ----
2268 } ----
2269 ----
2270 ReservedCycles.resize(NumUnits, InvalidCycle); 0
2271 } ----
2272 } 0
2273 ----
2274 /// Compute the stall cycles based on this SUnit's ready time. Heuristics treat ----
2275 /// these "soft stalls" differently than the hard stall cycles based on CPU ----
2276 /// resources and computed by checkHazard(). A fully in-order model ----
2277 /// (MicroOpBufferSize==0) will not make use of this since instructions are not ----
2278 /// available for scheduling until they are ready. However, a weaker in-order ----
2279 /// model may use this for heuristics. For example, if a processor has in-order ----
2280 /// behavior when reading certain resources, this may come into play. ----
2281 unsigned SchedBoundary::getLatencyStallCycles(SUnit *SU) { 0
2282 if (!SU->isUnbuffered) 0
2283 return 0; 0
2284 ----
2285 unsigned ReadyCycle = (isTop() ? SU->TopReadyCycle : SU->BotReadyCycle); 0
2286 if (ReadyCycle > CurrCycle) 0
2287 return ReadyCycle - CurrCycle; 0
2288 return 0; 0
2289 } ----
2290 ----
2291 /// Compute the next cycle at which the given processor resource unit ----
2292 /// can be scheduled. ----
2293 unsigned SchedBoundary::getNextResourceCycleByInstance(unsigned InstanceIdx, 0
2294 unsigned Cycles, ----
2295 unsigned StartAtCycle) { ----
2296 if (SchedModel && SchedModel->enableIntervals()) { 0
2297 if (isTop()) 0
2298 return ReservedResourceSegments[InstanceIdx].getFirstAvailableAtFromTop( 0
2299 CurrCycle, StartAtCycle, Cycles); 0
2300 ----
2301 return ReservedResourceSegments[InstanceIdx].getFirstAvailableAtFromBottom( 0
2302 CurrCycle, StartAtCycle, Cycles); 0
2303 } ----
2304 ----
2305 unsigned NextUnreserved = ReservedCycles[InstanceIdx]; 0
2306 // If this resource has never been used, always return cycle zero. ----
2307 if (NextUnreserved == InvalidCycle) 0
2308 return CurrCycle; 0
2309 // For bottom-up scheduling add the cycles needed for the current operation. ----
2310 if (!isTop()) 0
2311 NextUnreserved = std::max(CurrCycle, NextUnreserved + Cycles); 0
2312 return NextUnreserved; 0
2313 } ----
2314 ----
2315 /// Compute the next cycle at which the given processor resource can be ----
2316 /// scheduled. Returns the next cycle and the index of the processor resource ----
2317 /// instance in the reserved cycles vector. ----
2318 std::pair ----
2319 SchedBoundary::getNextResourceCycle(const MCSchedClassDesc *SC, unsigned PIdx, 0
2320 unsigned Cycles, unsigned StartAtCycle) { ----
2321 if (MischedDetailResourceBooking) { 0
2322 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Resource booking (@" << CurrCycle << "c): \n"); 0
2323 LLVM_DEBUG(dumpReservedCycles()); 0
2324 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " getNextResourceCycle (@" << CurrCycle << "c): \n"); 0
2325 } ----
2326 unsigned MinNextUnreserved = InvalidCycle; 0
2327 unsigned InstanceIdx = 0; 0
2328 unsigned StartIndex = ReservedCyclesIndex[PIdx]; 0
2329 unsigned NumberOfInstances = SchedModel->getProcResource(PIdx)->NumUnits; 0
2330 assert(NumberOfInstances > 0 && 0
2331 "Cannot have zero instances of a ProcResource"); ----
2332 ----
2333 if (isUnbufferedGroup(PIdx)) { 0
2334 // If any subunits are used by the instruction, report that the resource ----
2335 // group is available at 0, effectively removing the group record from ----
2336 // hazarding and basing the hazarding decisions on the subunit records. ----
2337 // Otherwise, choose the first available instance from among the subunits. ----
2338 // Specifications which assign cycles to both the subunits and the group or ----
2339 // which use an unbuffered group with buffered subunits will appear to ----
2340 // schedule strangely. In the first case, the additional cycles for the ----
2341 // group will be ignored. In the second, the group will be ignored ----
2342 // entirely. ----
2343 for (const MCWriteProcResEntry &PE : 0
2344 make_range(SchedModel->getWriteProcResBegin(SC), 0
2345 SchedModel->getWriteProcResEnd(SC))) 0
2346 if (ResourceGroupSubUnitMasks[PIdx][PE.ProcResourceIdx]) 0
2347 return std::make_pair(0u, StartIndex); 0
2348 ----
2349 auto SubUnits = SchedModel->getProcResource(PIdx)->SubUnitsIdxBegin; 0
2350 for (unsigned I = 0, End = NumberOfInstances; I < End; ++I) { 0
2351 unsigned NextUnreserved, NextInstanceIdx; ----
2352 std::tie(NextUnreserved, NextInstanceIdx) = 0
2353 getNextResourceCycle(SC, SubUnits[I], Cycles, StartAtCycle); 0
2354 if (MinNextUnreserved > NextUnreserved) { 0
2355 InstanceIdx = NextInstanceIdx; 0
2356 MinNextUnreserved = NextUnreserved; 0
2357 } ----
2358 } ----
2359 return std::make_pair(MinNextUnreserved, InstanceIdx); 0
2360 } ----
2361 ----
2362 for (unsigned I = StartIndex, End = StartIndex + NumberOfInstances; I < End; 0
2363 ++I) { ----
2364 unsigned NextUnreserved = ----
2365 getNextResourceCycleByInstance(I, Cycles, StartAtCycle); 0
2366 if (MischedDetailResourceBooking) 0
2367 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Instance " << I - StartIndex << " available @" 0
2368 << NextUnreserved << "c\n"); ----
2369 if (MinNextUnreserved > NextUnreserved) { 0
2370 InstanceIdx = I; 0
2371 MinNextUnreserved = NextUnreserved; 0
2372 } ----
2373 } ----
2374 if (MischedDetailResourceBooking) 0
2375 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " selecting " << SchedModel->getResourceName(PIdx) 0
2376 << "[" << InstanceIdx - StartIndex << "]" ----
2377 << " available @" << MinNextUnreserved << "c" ----
2378 << "\n"); ----
2379 return std::make_pair(MinNextUnreserved, InstanceIdx); 0
2380 } ----
2381 ----
2382 /// Does this SU have a hazard within the current instruction group. ----
2383 /// ----
2384 /// The scheduler supports two modes of hazard recognition. The first is the ----
2385 /// ScheduleHazardRecognizer API. It is a fully general hazard recognizer that ----
2386 /// supports highly complicated in-order reservation tables ----
2387 /// (ScoreboardHazardRecognizer) and arbitrary target-specific logic. ----
2388 /// ----
2389 /// The second is a streamlined mechanism that checks for hazards based on ----
2390 /// simple counters that the scheduler itself maintains. It explicitly checks ----
2391 /// for instruction dispatch limitations, including the number of micro-ops that ----
2392 /// can dispatch per cycle. ----
2393 /// ----
2394 /// TODO: Also check whether the SU must start a new group. ----
2395 bool SchedBoundary::checkHazard(SUnit *SU) { 0
2396 if (HazardRec->isEnabled() 0
2397 && HazardRec->getHazardType(SU) != ScheduleHazardRecognizer::NoHazard) { 0
2398 return true; 0
2399 } ----
2400 ----
2401 unsigned uops = SchedModel->getNumMicroOps(SU->getInstr()); 0
2402 if ((CurrMOps > 0) && (CurrMOps + uops > SchedModel->getIssueWidth())) { 0
2403 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " SU(" << SU->NodeNum << ") uops=" 0
2404 << SchedModel->getNumMicroOps(SU->getInstr()) << '\n'); ----
2405 return true; 0
2406 } ----
2407 ----
2408 if (CurrMOps > 0 && 0
2409 ((isTop() && SchedModel->mustBeginGroup(SU->getInstr())) || 0
2410 (!isTop() && SchedModel->mustEndGroup(SU->getInstr())))) { 0
2411 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " hazard: SU(" << SU->NodeNum << ") must " 0
2412 << (isTop() ? "begin" : "end") << " group\n"); ----
2413 return true; 0
2414 } ----
2415 ----
2416 if (SchedModel->hasInstrSchedModel() && SU->hasReservedResource) { 0
2417 const MCSchedClassDesc *SC = DAG->getSchedClass(SU); 0
2418 for (const MCWriteProcResEntry &PE : 0
2419 make_range(SchedModel->getWriteProcResBegin(SC), 0
2420 SchedModel->getWriteProcResEnd(SC))) { 0
2421 unsigned ResIdx = PE.ProcResourceIdx; 0
2422 unsigned Cycles = PE.Cycles; 0
2423 unsigned StartAtCycle = PE.StartAtCycle; 0
2424 unsigned NRCycle, InstanceIdx; ----
2425 std::tie(NRCycle, InstanceIdx) = 0
2426 getNextResourceCycle(SC, ResIdx, Cycles, StartAtCycle); 0
2427 if (NRCycle > CurrCycle) { 0
2428 #if LLVM_ENABLE_ABI_BREAKING_CHECKS ----
2429 MaxObservedStall = std::max(Cycles, MaxObservedStall); 0
2430 #endif ----
2431 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " SU(" << SU->NodeNum << ") " 0
2432 << SchedModel->getResourceName(ResIdx) ----
2433 << '[' << InstanceIdx - ReservedCyclesIndex[ResIdx] << ']' ----
2434 << "=" << NRCycle << "c\n"); ----
2435 return true; 0
2436 } ----
2437 } ----
2438 } ----
2439 return false; 0
2440 } ----
2441 ----
2442 // Find the unscheduled node in ReadySUs with the highest latency. ----
2443 unsigned SchedBoundary:: 0
2444 findMaxLatency(ArrayRef ReadySUs) { ----
2445 SUnit *LateSU = nullptr; 0
2446 unsigned RemLatency = 0; 0
2447 for (SUnit *SU : ReadySUs) { 0
2448 unsigned L = getUnscheduledLatency(SU); 0
2449 if (L > RemLatency) { 0
2450 RemLatency = L; 0
2451 LateSU = SU; 0
2452 } ----
2453 } ----
2454 if (LateSU) { 0
2455 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Available.getName() << " RemLatency SU(" 0
2456 << LateSU->NodeNum << ") " << RemLatency << "c\n"); ----
2457 } ----
2458 return RemLatency; 0
2459 } ----
2460 ----
2461 // Count resources in this zone and the remaining unscheduled ----
2462 // instruction. Return the max count, scaled. Set OtherCritIdx to the critical ----
2463 // resource index, or zero if the zone is issue limited. ----
2464 unsigned SchedBoundary:: 0
2465 getOtherResourceCount(unsigned &OtherCritIdx) { ----
2466 OtherCritIdx = 0; 0
2467 if (!SchedModel->hasInstrSchedModel()) 0
2468 return 0; 0
2469 ----
2470 unsigned OtherCritCount = Rem->RemIssueCount 0
2471 + (RetiredMOps * SchedModel->getMicroOpFactor()); 0
2472 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " " << Available.getName() << " + Remain MOps: " 0
2473 << OtherCritCount / SchedModel->getMicroOpFactor() << '\n'); ----
2474 for (unsigned PIdx = 1, PEnd = SchedModel->getNumProcResourceKinds(); 0
2475 PIdx != PEnd; ++PIdx) { 0
2476 unsigned OtherCount = getResourceCount(PIdx) + Rem->RemainingCounts[PIdx]; 0
2477 if (OtherCount > OtherCritCount) { 0
2478 OtherCritCount = OtherCount; 0
2479 OtherCritIdx = PIdx; 0
2480 } ----
2481 } ----
2482 if (OtherCritIdx) { 0
2483 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
2484 dbgs() << " " << Available.getName() << " + Remain CritRes: " ----
2485 << OtherCritCount / SchedModel->getResourceFactor(OtherCritIdx) ----
2486 << " " << SchedModel->getResourceName(OtherCritIdx) << "\n"); ----
2487 } ----
2488 return OtherCritCount; 0
2489 } ----
2490 ----
2491 void SchedBoundary::releaseNode(SUnit *SU, unsigned ReadyCycle, bool InPQueue, 0
2492 unsigned Idx) { ----
2493 assert(SU->getInstr() && "Scheduled SUnit must have instr"); 0
2494 ----
2495 #if LLVM_ENABLE_ABI_BREAKING_CHECKS ----
2496 // ReadyCycle was been bumped up to the CurrCycle when this node was ----
2497 // scheduled, but CurrCycle may have been eagerly advanced immediately after ----
2498 // scheduling, so may now be greater than ReadyCycle. ----
2499 if (ReadyCycle > CurrCycle) 0
2500 MaxObservedStall = std::max(ReadyCycle - CurrCycle, MaxObservedStall); 0
2501 #endif ----
2502 ----
2503 if (ReadyCycle < MinReadyCycle) 0
2504 MinReadyCycle = ReadyCycle; 0
2505 ----
2506 // Check for interlocks first. For the purpose of other heuristics, an ----
2507 // instruction that cannot issue appears as if it's not in the ReadyQueue. ----
2508 bool IsBuffered = SchedModel->getMicroOpBufferSize() != 0; 0
2509 bool HazardDetected = (!IsBuffered && ReadyCycle > CurrCycle) || 0
2510 checkHazard(SU) || (Available.size() >= ReadyListLimit); 0
2511 ----
2512 if (!HazardDetected) { 0
2513 Available.push(SU); 0
2514 ----
2515 if (InPQueue) 0
2516 Pending.remove(Pending.begin() + Idx); 0
2517 return; 0
2518 } ----
2519 ----
2520 if (!InPQueue) 0
2521 Pending.push(SU); 0
2522 } ----
2523 ----
2524 /// Move the boundary of scheduled code by one cycle. ----
2525 void SchedBoundary::bumpCycle(unsigned NextCycle) { 0
2526 if (SchedModel->getMicroOpBufferSize() == 0) { 0
2527 assert(MinReadyCycle < std::numeric_limits::max() && 0
2528 "MinReadyCycle uninitialized"); ----
2529 if (MinReadyCycle > NextCycle) 0
2530 NextCycle = MinReadyCycle; 0
2531 } ----
2532 // Update the current micro-ops, which will issue in the next cycle. ----
2533 unsigned DecMOps = SchedModel->getIssueWidth() * (NextCycle - CurrCycle); 0
2534 CurrMOps = (CurrMOps <= DecMOps) ? 0 : CurrMOps - DecMOps; 0
2535 ----
2536 // Decrement DependentLatency based on the next cycle. ----
2537 if ((NextCycle - CurrCycle) > DependentLatency) 0
2538 DependentLatency = 0; 0
2539 else ----
2540 DependentLatency -= (NextCycle - CurrCycle); 0
2541 ----
2542 if (!HazardRec->isEnabled()) { 0
2543 // Bypass HazardRec virtual calls. ----
2544 CurrCycle = NextCycle; 0
2545 } else { ----
2546 // Bypass getHazardType calls in case of long latency. ----
2547 for (; CurrCycle != NextCycle; ++CurrCycle) { 0
2548 if (isTop()) 0
2549 HazardRec->AdvanceCycle(); 0
2550 else ----
2551 HazardRec->RecedeCycle(); 0
2552 } ----
2553 } ----
2554 CheckPending = true; 0
2555 IsResourceLimited = 0
2556 checkResourceLimit(SchedModel->getLatencyFactor(), getCriticalCount(), 0
2557 getScheduledLatency(), true); ----
2558 ----
2559 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Cycle: " << CurrCycle << ' ' << Available.getName() 0
2560 << '\n'); ----
2561 } 0
2562 ----
2563 void SchedBoundary::incExecutedResources(unsigned PIdx, unsigned Count) { 0
2564 ExecutedResCounts[PIdx] += Count; 0
2565 if (ExecutedResCounts[PIdx] > MaxExecutedResCount) 0
2566 MaxExecutedResCount = ExecutedResCounts[PIdx]; 0
2567 } 0
2568 ----
2569 /// Add the given processor resource to this scheduled zone. ----
2570 /// ----
2571 /// \param Cycles indicates the number of consecutive (non-pipelined) cycles ----
2572 /// during which this resource is consumed. ----
2573 /// ----
2574 /// \return the next cycle at which the instruction may execute without ----
2575 /// oversubscribing resources. ----
2576 unsigned SchedBoundary::countResource(const MCSchedClassDesc *SC, unsigned PIdx, 0
2577 unsigned Cycles, unsigned NextCycle, ----
2578 unsigned StartAtCycle) { ----
2579 unsigned Factor = SchedModel->getResourceFactor(PIdx); 0
2580 unsigned Count = Factor * (Cycles - StartAtCycle); 0
2581 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " " << SchedModel->getResourceName(PIdx) << " +" 0
2582 << Cycles << "x" << Factor << "u\n"); ----
2583 ----
2584 // Update Executed resources counts. ----
2585 incExecutedResources(PIdx, Count); 0
2586 assert(Rem->RemainingCounts[PIdx] >= Count && "resource double counted"); 0
2587 Rem->RemainingCounts[PIdx] -= Count; 0
2588 ----
2589 // Check if this resource exceeds the current critical resource. If so, it ----
2590 // becomes the critical resource. ----
2591 if (ZoneCritResIdx != PIdx && (getResourceCount(PIdx) > getCriticalCount())) { 0
2592 ZoneCritResIdx = PIdx; 0
2593 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " *** Critical resource " 0
2594 << SchedModel->getResourceName(PIdx) << ": " ----
2595 << getResourceCount(PIdx) / SchedModel->getLatencyFactor() ----
2596 << "c\n"); ----
2597 } ----
2598 // For reserved resources, record the highest cycle using the resource. ----
2599 unsigned NextAvailable, InstanceIdx; ----
2600 std::tie(NextAvailable, InstanceIdx) = 0
2601 getNextResourceCycle(SC, PIdx, Cycles, StartAtCycle); 0
2602 if (NextAvailable > CurrCycle) { 0
2603 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Resource conflict: " 0
2604 << SchedModel->getResourceName(PIdx) ----
2605 << '[' << InstanceIdx - ReservedCyclesIndex[PIdx] << ']' ----
2606 << " reserved until @" << NextAvailable << "\n"); ----
2607 } ----
2608 return NextAvailable; 0
2609 } ----
2610 ----
2611 /// Move the boundary of scheduled code by one SUnit. ----
2612 void SchedBoundary::bumpNode(SUnit *SU) { 0
2613 // Update the reservation table. ----
2614 if (HazardRec->isEnabled()) { 0
2615 if (!isTop() && SU->isCall) { 0
2616 // Calls are scheduled with their preceding instructions. For bottom-up ----
2617 // scheduling, clear the pipeline state before emitting. ----
2618 HazardRec->Reset(); 0
2619 } ----
2620 HazardRec->EmitInstruction(SU); 0
2621 // Scheduling an instruction may have made pending instructions available. ----
2622 CheckPending = true; 0
2623 } ----
2624 // checkHazard should prevent scheduling multiple instructions per cycle that ----
2625 // exceed the issue width. ----
2626 const MCSchedClassDesc *SC = DAG->getSchedClass(SU); 0
2627 unsigned IncMOps = SchedModel->getNumMicroOps(SU->getInstr()); 0
2628 assert( 0
2629 (CurrMOps == 0 || (CurrMOps + IncMOps) <= SchedModel->getIssueWidth()) && ----
2630 "Cannot schedule this instruction's MicroOps in the current cycle."); ----
2631 ----
2632 unsigned ReadyCycle = (isTop() ? SU->TopReadyCycle : SU->BotReadyCycle); 0
2633 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Ready @" << ReadyCycle << "c\n"); 0
2634 ----
2635 unsigned NextCycle = CurrCycle; 0
2636 switch (SchedModel->getMicroOpBufferSize()) { 0
2637 case 0: 0
2638 assert(ReadyCycle <= CurrCycle && "Broken PendingQueue"); 0
2639 break; 0
2640 case 1: 0
2641 if (ReadyCycle > NextCycle) { 0
2642 NextCycle = ReadyCycle; 0
2643 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " *** Stall until: " << ReadyCycle << "\n"); 0
2644 } ----
2645 break; 0
2646 default: 0
2647 // We don't currently model the OOO reorder buffer, so consider all ----
2648 // scheduled MOps to be "retired". We do loosely model in-order resource ----
2649 // latency. If this instruction uses an in-order resource, account for any ----
2650 // likely stall cycles. ----
2651 if (SU->isUnbuffered && ReadyCycle > NextCycle) 0
2652 NextCycle = ReadyCycle; 0
2653 break; 0
2654 } ----
2655 RetiredMOps += IncMOps; 0
2656 ----
2657 // Update resource counts and critical resource. ----
2658 if (SchedModel->hasInstrSchedModel()) { 0
2659 unsigned DecRemIssue = IncMOps * SchedModel->getMicroOpFactor(); 0
2660 assert(Rem->RemIssueCount >= DecRemIssue && "MOps double counted"); 0
2661 Rem->RemIssueCount -= DecRemIssue; 0
2662 if (ZoneCritResIdx) { 0
2663 // Scale scheduled micro-ops for comparing with the critical resource. ----
2664 unsigned ScaledMOps = ----
2665 RetiredMOps * SchedModel->getMicroOpFactor(); 0
2666 ----
2667 // If scaled micro-ops are now more than the previous critical resource by ----
2668 // a full cycle, then micro-ops issue becomes critical. ----
2669 if ((int)(ScaledMOps - getResourceCount(ZoneCritResIdx)) 0
2670 >= (int)SchedModel->getLatencyFactor()) { 0
2671 ZoneCritResIdx = 0; 0
2672 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " *** Critical resource NumMicroOps: " 0
2673 << ScaledMOps / SchedModel->getLatencyFactor() ----
2674 << "c\n"); ----
2675 } ----
2676 } ----
2677 for (TargetSchedModel::ProcResIter 0
2678 PI = SchedModel->getWriteProcResBegin(SC), 0
2679 PE = SchedModel->getWriteProcResEnd(SC); PI != PE; ++PI) { 0
2680 unsigned RCycle = countResource(SC, PI->ProcResourceIdx, PI->Cycles, 0
2681 NextCycle, PI->StartAtCycle); 0
2682 if (RCycle > NextCycle) 0
2683 NextCycle = RCycle; 0
2684 } ----
2685 if (SU->hasReservedResource) { 0
2686 // For reserved resources, record the highest cycle using the resource. ----
2687 // For top-down scheduling, this is the cycle in which we schedule this ----
2688 // instruction plus the number of cycles the operations reserves the ----
2689 // resource. For bottom-up is it simply the instruction's cycle. ----
2690 for (TargetSchedModel::ProcResIter 0
2691 PI = SchedModel->getWriteProcResBegin(SC), 0
2692 PE = SchedModel->getWriteProcResEnd(SC); PI != PE; ++PI) { 0
2693 unsigned PIdx = PI->ProcResourceIdx; 0
2694 if (SchedModel->getProcResource(PIdx)->BufferSize == 0) { 0
2695 ----
2696 if (SchedModel && SchedModel->enableIntervals()) { 0
2697 unsigned ReservedUntil, InstanceIdx; ----
2698 std::tie(ReservedUntil, InstanceIdx) = 0
2699 getNextResourceCycle(SC, PIdx, PI->Cycles, PI->StartAtCycle); 0
2700 if (isTop()) { 0
2701 ReservedResourceSegments[InstanceIdx].add( 0
2702 ResourceSegments::getResourceIntervalTop( ----
2703 NextCycle, PI->StartAtCycle, PI->Cycles), 0
2704 MIResourceCutOff); ----
2705 } else { ----
2706 ReservedResourceSegments[InstanceIdx].add( 0
2707 ResourceSegments::getResourceIntervalBottom( ----
2708 NextCycle, PI->StartAtCycle, PI->Cycles), 0
2709 MIResourceCutOff); ----
2710 } ----
2711 } else { ----
2712 ----
2713 unsigned ReservedUntil, InstanceIdx; ----
2714 std::tie(ReservedUntil, InstanceIdx) = 0
2715 getNextResourceCycle(SC, PIdx, PI->Cycles, PI->StartAtCycle); 0
2716 if (isTop()) { 0
2717 ReservedCycles[InstanceIdx] = 0
2718 std::max(ReservedUntil, NextCycle + PI->Cycles); 0
2719 } else ----
2720 ReservedCycles[InstanceIdx] = NextCycle; 0
2721 } ----
2722 } ----
2723 } ----
2724 } ----
2725 } ----
2726 // Update ExpectedLatency and DependentLatency. ----
2727 unsigned &TopLatency = isTop() ? ExpectedLatency : DependentLatency; 0
2728 unsigned &BotLatency = isTop() ? DependentLatency : ExpectedLatency; 0
2729 if (SU->getDepth() > TopLatency) { 0
2730 TopLatency = SU->getDepth(); 0
2731 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " " << Available.getName() << " TopLatency SU(" 0
2732 << SU->NodeNum << ") " << TopLatency << "c\n"); ----
2733 } ----
2734 if (SU->getHeight() > BotLatency) { 0
2735 BotLatency = SU->getHeight(); 0
2736 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " " << Available.getName() << " BotLatency SU(" 0
2737 << SU->NodeNum << ") " << BotLatency << "c\n"); ----
2738 } ----
2739 // If we stall for any reason, bump the cycle. ----
2740 if (NextCycle > CurrCycle) 0
2741 bumpCycle(NextCycle); 0
2742 else ----
2743 // After updating ZoneCritResIdx and ExpectedLatency, check if we're ----
2744 // resource limited. If a stall occurred, bumpCycle does this. ----
2745 IsResourceLimited = 0
2746 checkResourceLimit(SchedModel->getLatencyFactor(), getCriticalCount(), 0
2747 getScheduledLatency(), true); ----
2748 ----
2749 // Update CurrMOps after calling bumpCycle to handle stalls, since bumpCycle ----
2750 // resets CurrMOps. Loop to handle instructions with more MOps than issue in ----
2751 // one cycle. Since we commonly reach the max MOps here, opportunistically ----
2752 // bump the cycle to avoid uselessly checking everything in the readyQ. ----
2753 CurrMOps += IncMOps; 0
2754 ----
2755 // Bump the cycle count for issue group constraints. ----
2756 // This must be done after NextCycle has been adjust for all other stalls. ----
2757 // Calling bumpCycle(X) will reduce CurrMOps by one issue group and set ----
2758 // currCycle to X. ----
2759 if ((isTop() && SchedModel->mustEndGroup(SU->getInstr())) || 0
2760 (!isTop() && SchedModel->mustBeginGroup(SU->getInstr()))) { 0
2761 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Bump cycle to " << (isTop() ? "end" : "begin") 0
2762 << " group\n"); ----
2763 bumpCycle(++NextCycle); 0
2764 } ----
2765 ----
2766 while (CurrMOps >= SchedModel->getIssueWidth()) { 0
2767 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " *** Max MOps " << CurrMOps << " at cycle " 0
2768 << CurrCycle << '\n'); ----
2769 bumpCycle(++NextCycle); 0
2770 } ----
2771 LLVM_DEBUG(dumpScheduledState()); 0
2772 } 0
2773 ----
2774 /// Release pending ready nodes in to the available queue. This makes them ----
2775 /// visible to heuristics. ----
2776 void SchedBoundary::releasePending() { 0
2777 // If the available queue is empty, it is safe to reset MinReadyCycle. ----
2778 if (Available.empty()) 0
2779 MinReadyCycle = std::numeric_limits::max(); 0
2780 ----
2781 // Check to see if any of the pending instructions are ready to issue. If ----
2782 // so, add them to the available queue. ----
2783 for (unsigned I = 0, E = Pending.size(); I < E; ++I) { 0
2784 SUnit *SU = *(Pending.begin() + I); 0
2785 unsigned ReadyCycle = isTop() ? SU->TopReadyCycle : SU->BotReadyCycle; 0
2786 ----
2787 if (ReadyCycle < MinReadyCycle) 0
2788 MinReadyCycle = ReadyCycle; 0
2789 ----
2790 if (Available.size() >= ReadyListLimit) 0
2791 break; 0
2792 ----
2793 releaseNode(SU, ReadyCycle, true, I); 0
2794 if (E != Pending.size()) { 0
2795 --I; 0
2796 --E; 0
2797 } ----
2798 } ----
2799 CheckPending = false; 0
2800 } 0
2801 ----
2802 /// Remove SU from the ready set for this boundary. ----
2803 void SchedBoundary::removeReady(SUnit *SU) { 0
2804 if (Available.isInQueue(SU)) 0
2805 Available.remove(Available.find(SU)); 0
2806 else { ----
2807 assert(Pending.isInQueue(SU) && "bad ready count"); 0
2808 Pending.remove(Pending.find(SU)); 0
2809 } ----
2810 } 0
2811 ----
2812 /// If this queue only has one ready candidate, return it. As a side effect, ----
2813 /// defer any nodes that now hit a hazard, and advance the cycle until at least ----
2814 /// one node is ready. If multiple instructions are ready, return NULL. ----
2815 SUnit *SchedBoundary::pickOnlyChoice() { 0
2816 if (CheckPending) 0
2817 releasePending(); 0
2818 ----
2819 // Defer any ready instrs that now have a hazard. ----
2820 for (ReadyQueue::iterator I = Available.begin(); I != Available.end();) { 0
2821 if (checkHazard(*I)) { 0
2822 Pending.push(*I); 0
2823 I = Available.remove(I); 0
2824 continue; 0
2825 } ----
2826 ++I; 0
2827 } ----
2828 for (unsigned i = 0; Available.empty(); ++i) { 0
2829 // FIXME: Re-enable assert once PR20057 is resolved. ----
2830 // assert(i <= (HazardRec->getMaxLookAhead() + MaxObservedStall) && ----
2831 // "permanent hazard"); ----
2832 (void)i; ----
2833 bumpCycle(CurrCycle + 1); 0
2834 releasePending(); 0
2835 } ----
2836 ----
2837 LLVM_DEBUG(Pending.dump()); 0
2838 LLVM_DEBUG(Available.dump()); 0
2839 ----
2840 if (Available.size() == 1) 0
2841 return *Available.begin(); 0
2842 return nullptr; 0
2843 } ----
2844 ----
2845 #if !defined(NDEBUG) || defined(LLVM_ENABLE_DUMP) ----
2846 ----
2847 /// Dump the content of the \ref ReservedCycles vector for the ----
2848 /// resources that are used in the basic block. ----
2849 /// ----
2850 LLVM_DUMP_METHOD void SchedBoundary::dumpReservedCycles() const { 0
2851 if (!SchedModel->hasInstrSchedModel()) 0
2852 return; 0
2853 ----
2854 unsigned ResourceCount = SchedModel->getNumProcResourceKinds(); 0
2855 unsigned StartIdx = 0; 0
2856 ----
2857 for (unsigned ResIdx = 0; ResIdx < ResourceCount; ++ResIdx) { 0
2858 const unsigned NumUnits = SchedModel->getProcResource(ResIdx)->NumUnits; 0
2859 std::string ResName = SchedModel->getResourceName(ResIdx); 0
2860 for (unsigned UnitIdx = 0; UnitIdx < NumUnits; ++UnitIdx) { 0
2861 dbgs() << ResName << "(" << UnitIdx << ") = "; 0
2862 if (SchedModel && SchedModel->enableIntervals()) { 0
2863 if (ReservedResourceSegments.count(StartIdx + UnitIdx)) 0
2864 dbgs() << ReservedResourceSegments.at(StartIdx + UnitIdx); 0
2865 else ----
2866 dbgs() << "{ }\n"; 0
2867 } else ----
2868 dbgs() << ReservedCycles[StartIdx + UnitIdx] << "\n"; 0
2869 } ----
2870 StartIdx += NumUnits; 0
2871 } 0
2872 } ----

2874 // This is useful information to dump after bumpNode. ----
2875 // Note that the Queue contents are more useful before pickNodeFromQueue. ----
2876 LLVM_DUMP_METHOD void SchedBoundary::dumpScheduledState() const { 0
2877 unsigned ResFactor; ----
2878 unsigned ResCount; ----
2879 if (ZoneCritResIdx) { 0
2880 ResFactor = SchedModel->getResourceFactor(ZoneCritResIdx); 0
2881 ResCount = getResourceCount(ZoneCritResIdx); 0
2882 } else { ----
2883 ResFactor = SchedModel->getMicroOpFactor(); 0
2884 ResCount = RetiredMOps * ResFactor; 0
2885 } ----

2887 dbgs() << Available.getName() << " @" << CurrCycle << "c\n" 0

2901 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
2902 // GenericScheduler - Generic implementation of MachineSchedStrategy. ----
2903 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
2904 ----
2905 void GenericSchedulerBase::SchedCandidate:: 0
2906 initResourceDelta(const ScheduleDAGMI *DAG, ----
2907 const TargetSchedModel *SchedModel) { ----
2908 if (!Policy.ReduceResIdx && !Policy.DemandResIdx) 0
2909 return; 0
2910 ----
2911 const MCSchedClassDesc *SC = DAG->getSchedClass(SU); 0
2912 for (TargetSchedModel::ProcResIter 0
2913 PI = SchedModel->getWriteProcResBegin(SC), 0
2914 PE = SchedModel->getWriteProcResEnd(SC); PI != PE; ++PI) { 0
2915 if (PI->ProcResourceIdx == Policy.ReduceResIdx) 0
2916 ResDelta.CritResources += PI->Cycles; 0
2917 if (PI->ProcResourceIdx == Policy.DemandResIdx) 0
2918 ResDelta.DemandedResources += PI->Cycles; 0
2919 } ----
2920 } ----
2921 ----
2922 /// Compute remaining latency. We need this both to determine whether the ----
2923 /// overall schedule has become latency-limited and whether the instructions ----
2924 /// outside this zone are resource or latency limited. ----
2925 /// ----
2926 /// The "dependent" latency is updated incrementally during scheduling as the ----
2927 /// max height/depth of scheduled nodes minus the cycles since it was ----
2928 /// scheduled: ----
2929 /// DLat = max (N.depth - (CurrCycle - N.ReadyCycle) for N in Zone ----
2930 /// ----
2931 /// The "independent" latency is the max ready queue depth: ----
2932 /// ILat = max N.depth for N in Available|Pending ----
2933 /// ----
2934 /// RemainingLatency is the greater of independent and dependent latency. ----
2935 /// ----
2936 /// These computations are expensive, especially in DAGs with many edges, so ----
2937 /// only do them if necessary. ----
2938 static unsigned computeRemLatency(SchedBoundary &CurrZone) { 0
2939 unsigned RemLatency = CurrZone.getDependentLatency(); 0
2940 RemLatency = std::max(RemLatency, 0
2941 CurrZone.findMaxLatency(CurrZone.Available.elements())); 0
2942 RemLatency = std::max(RemLatency, 0
2943 CurrZone.findMaxLatency(CurrZone.Pending.elements())); 0
2944 return RemLatency; 0
2945 } ----
2946 ----
2947 /// Returns true if the current cycle plus remaning latency is greater than ----
2948 /// the critical path in the scheduling region. ----
2949 bool GenericSchedulerBase::shouldReduceLatency(const CandPolicy &Policy, 0
2950 SchedBoundary &CurrZone, ----
2951 bool ComputeRemLatency, ----
2952 unsigned &RemLatency) const { ----
2953 // The current cycle is already greater than the critical path, so we are ----
2954 // already latency limited and don't need to compute the remaining latency. ----
2955 if (CurrZone.getCurrCycle() > Rem.CriticalPath) 0
2956 return true; 0
2957 ----
2958 // If we haven't scheduled anything yet, then we aren't latency limited. ----
2959 if (CurrZone.getCurrCycle() == 0) 0
2960 return false; 0
2961 ----
2962 if (ComputeRemLatency) 0
2963 RemLatency = computeRemLatency(CurrZone); 0
2964 ----
2965 return RemLatency + CurrZone.getCurrCycle() > Rem.CriticalPath; 0
2966 } ----
2967 ----
2968 /// Set the CandPolicy given a scheduling zone given the current resources and ----
2969 /// latencies inside and outside the zone. ----
2970 void GenericSchedulerBase::setPolicy(CandPolicy &Policy, bool IsPostRA, 0
2971 SchedBoundary &CurrZone, ----
2972 SchedBoundary *OtherZone) { ----
2973 // Apply preemptive heuristics based on the total latency and resources ----
2974 // inside and outside this zone. Potential stalls should be considered before ----
2975 // following this policy. ----
2976 ----
2977 // Compute the critical resource outside the zone. ----
2978 unsigned OtherCritIdx = 0; 0
2979 unsigned OtherCount = ----
2980 OtherZone ? OtherZone->getOtherResourceCount(OtherCritIdx) : 0; 0
2981 ----
2982 bool OtherResLimited = false; 0
2983 unsigned RemLatency = 0; 0
2984 bool RemLatencyComputed = false; 0
2985 if (SchedModel->hasInstrSchedModel() && OtherCount != 0) { 0
2986 RemLatency = computeRemLatency(CurrZone); 0
2987 RemLatencyComputed = true; 0
2988 OtherResLimited = checkResourceLimit(SchedModel->getLatencyFactor(), 0
2989 OtherCount, RemLatency, false); ----
2990 } ----
2991 ----
2992 // Schedule aggressively for latency in PostRA mode. We don't check for ----
2993 // acyclic latency during PostRA, and highly out-of-order processors will ----
2994 // skip PostRA scheduling. ----
2995 if (!OtherResLimited && 0
2996 (IsPostRA || shouldReduceLatency(Policy, CurrZone, !RemLatencyComputed, 0
2997 RemLatency))) { ----
2998 Policy.ReduceLatency |= true; 0
2999 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " " << CurrZone.Available.getName() 0
3000 << " RemainingLatency " << RemLatency << " + " ----
3001 << CurrZone.getCurrCycle() << "c > CritPath " ----
3002 << Rem.CriticalPath << "\n"); ----
3003 } ----
3004 // If the same resource is limiting inside and outside the zone, do nothing. ----
3005 if (CurrZone.getZoneCritResIdx() == OtherCritIdx) 0
3006 return; 0
3007 ----
3008 LLVM_DEBUG(if (CurrZone.isResourceLimited()) { 0
3009 dbgs() << " " << CurrZone.Available.getName() << " ResourceLimited: " ----
3010 << SchedModel->getResourceName(CurrZone.getZoneCritResIdx()) << "\n"; ----
3011 } if (OtherResLimited) dbgs() ----
3012 << " RemainingLimit: " ----
3013 << SchedModel->getResourceName(OtherCritIdx) << "\n"; ----
3014 if (!CurrZone.isResourceLimited() && !OtherResLimited) dbgs() ----
3015 << " Latency limited both directions.\n"); ----
3016 ----
3017 if (CurrZone.isResourceLimited() && !Policy.ReduceResIdx) 0
3018 Policy.ReduceResIdx = CurrZone.getZoneCritResIdx(); 0
3019 ----
3020 if (OtherResLimited) 0
3021 Policy.DemandResIdx = OtherCritIdx; 0
3022 } ----

3103 /// Return true if this heuristic determines order. ----
3104 /// TODO: Consider refactor return type of these functions as integer or enum, ----
3105 /// as we may need to differentiate whether TryCand is better than Cand. ----
3106 bool tryLess(int TryVal, int CandVal, 0
3107 GenericSchedulerBase::SchedCandidate &TryCand, ----
3108 GenericSchedulerBase::SchedCandidate &Cand, ----
3109 GenericSchedulerBase::CandReason Reason) { ----
3110 if (TryVal < CandVal) { 0
3111 TryCand.Reason = Reason; 0
3112 return true; 0
3113 } ----
3114 if (TryVal > CandVal) { 0
3115 if (Cand.Reason > Reason) 0
3116 Cand.Reason = Reason; 0
3117 return true; 0
3118 } ----
3119 return false; 0
3120 } ----
3121 ----
3122 bool tryGreater(int TryVal, int CandVal, 0
3123 GenericSchedulerBase::SchedCandidate &TryCand, ----
3124 GenericSchedulerBase::SchedCandidate &Cand, ----
3125 GenericSchedulerBase::CandReason Reason) { ----
3126 if (TryVal > CandVal) { 0
3127 TryCand.Reason = Reason; 0
3128 return true; 0
3129 } ----
3130 if (TryVal < CandVal) { 0
3131 if (Cand.Reason > Reason) 0
3132 Cand.Reason = Reason; 0
3133 return true; 0
3134 } ----
3135 return false; 0
3136 } ----
3137 ----
3138 bool tryLatency(GenericSchedulerBase::SchedCandidate &TryCand, 0
3139 GenericSchedulerBase::SchedCandidate &Cand, ----
3140 SchedBoundary &Zone) { ----
3141 if (Zone.isTop()) { 0
3142 // Prefer the candidate with the lesser depth, but only if one of them has ----
3143 // depth greater than the total latency scheduled so far, otherwise either ----
3144 // of them could be scheduled now with no stall. ----
3145 if (std::max(TryCand.SU->getDepth(), Cand.SU->getDepth()) > 0
3146 Zone.getScheduledLatency()) { 0
3147 if (tryLess(TryCand.SU->getDepth(), Cand.SU->getDepth(), 0
3148 TryCand, Cand, GenericSchedulerBase::TopDepthReduce)) ----
3149 return true; 0
3150 } ----
3151 if (tryGreater(TryCand.SU->getHeight(), Cand.SU->getHeight(), 0
3152 TryCand, Cand, GenericSchedulerBase::TopPathReduce)) ----
3153 return true; 0
3154 } else { ----
3155 // Prefer the candidate with the lesser height, but only if one of them has ----
3156 // height greater than the total latency scheduled so far, otherwise either ----
3157 // of them could be scheduled now with no stall. ----
3158 if (std::max(TryCand.SU->getHeight(), Cand.SU->getHeight()) > 0
3159 Zone.getScheduledLatency()) { 0
3160 if (tryLess(TryCand.SU->getHeight(), Cand.SU->getHeight(), 0
3161 TryCand, Cand, GenericSchedulerBase::BotHeightReduce)) ----
3162 return true; 0
3163 } ----
3164 if (tryGreater(TryCand.SU->getDepth(), Cand.SU->getDepth(), 0
3165 TryCand, Cand, GenericSchedulerBase::BotPathReduce)) ----
3166 return true; 0
3167 } ----
3168 return false; 0
3169 } ----
3170 } // end namespace llvm ----

3214 /// Initialize the per-region scheduling policy. ----
3215 void GenericScheduler::initPolicy(MachineBasicBlock::iterator Begin, 0
3216 MachineBasicBlock::iterator End, ----
3217 unsigned NumRegionInstrs) { ----
3218 const MachineFunction &MF = *Begin->getMF(); 0
3219 const TargetLowering *TLI = MF.getSubtarget().getTargetLowering(); 0
3220 ----
3221 // Avoid setting up the register pressure tracker for small regions to save ----
3222 // compile time. As a rough heuristic, only track pressure when the number of ----
3223 // schedulable instructions exceeds half the integer register file. ----
3224 RegionPolicy.ShouldTrackPressure = true; 0
3225 for (unsigned VT = MVT::i32; VT > (unsigned)MVT::i1; --VT) { 0
3226 MVT::SimpleValueType LegalIntVT = (MVT::SimpleValueType)VT; 0
3227 if (TLI->isTypeLegal(LegalIntVT)) { 0
3228 unsigned NIntRegs = Context->RegClassInfo->getNumAllocatableRegs( 0
3229 TLI->getRegClassFor(LegalIntVT)); 0
3230 RegionPolicy.ShouldTrackPressure = NumRegionInstrs > (NIntRegs / 2); 0
3231 } ----
3232 } ----
3233 ----
3234 // For generic targets, we default to bottom-up, because it's simpler and more ----
3235 // compile-time optimizations have been implemented in that direction. ----
3236 RegionPolicy.OnlyBottomUp = true; 0
3237 ----
3238 // Allow the subtarget to override default policy. ----
3239 MF.getSubtarget().overrideSchedPolicy(RegionPolicy, NumRegionInstrs); 0
3240 ----
3241 // After subtarget overrides, apply command line options. ----
3242 if (!EnableRegPressure) { 0
3243 RegionPolicy.ShouldTrackPressure = false; 0
3244 RegionPolicy.ShouldTrackLaneMasks = false; 0
3245 } ----
3246 ----
3247 // Check -misched-topdown/bottomup can force or unforce scheduling direction. ----
3248 // e.g. -misched-bottomup=false allows scheduling in both directions. ----
3249 assert((!ForceTopDown || !ForceBottomUp) && 0
3250 "-misched-topdown incompatible with -misched-bottomup"); ----
3251 if (ForceBottomUp.getNumOccurrences() > 0) { 0
3252 RegionPolicy.OnlyBottomUp = ForceBottomUp; 0
3253 if (RegionPolicy.OnlyBottomUp) 0
3254 RegionPolicy.OnlyTopDown = false; 0
3255 } ----
3256 if (ForceTopDown.getNumOccurrences() > 0) { 0
3257 RegionPolicy.OnlyTopDown = ForceTopDown; 0
3258 if (RegionPolicy.OnlyTopDown) 0
3259 RegionPolicy.OnlyBottomUp = false; 0
3260 } ----
3261 } 0
3262 ----
3263 void GenericScheduler::dumpPolicy() const { 0
3264 // Cannot completely remove virtual function even in release mode. ----
3265 #if !defined(NDEBUG) || defined(LLVM_ENABLE_DUMP) ----
3266 dbgs() << "GenericScheduler RegionPolicy: " 0
3267 << " ShouldTrackPressure=" << RegionPolicy.ShouldTrackPressure 0
3268 << " OnlyTopDown=" << RegionPolicy.OnlyTopDown 0
3269 << " OnlyBottomUp=" << RegionPolicy.OnlyBottomUp 0
3270 << "\n"; 0
3271 #endif ----
3272 } 0
3273 ----
3274 /// Set IsAcyclicLatencyLimited if the acyclic path is longer than the cyclic ----
3275 /// critical path by more cycles than it takes to drain the instruction buffer. ----
3276 /// We estimate an upper bounds on in-flight instructions as: ----
3277 /// ----
3278 /// CyclesPerIteration = max( CyclicPath, Loop-Resource-Height ) ----
3279 /// InFlightIterations = AcyclicPath / CyclesPerIteration ----
3280 /// InFlightResources = InFlightIterations * LoopResources ----
3281 /// ----
3282 /// TODO: Check execution resources in addition to IssueCount. ----
3283 void GenericScheduler::checkAcyclicLatency() { 0
3284 if (Rem.CyclicCritPath == 0 || Rem.CyclicCritPath >= Rem.CriticalPath) 0
3285 return; 0
3286 ----
3287 // Scaled number of cycles per loop iteration. ----
3288 unsigned IterCount = ----
3289 std::max(Rem.CyclicCritPath * SchedModel->getLatencyFactor(), 0
3290 Rem.RemIssueCount); 0
3291 // Scaled acyclic critical path. ----
3292 unsigned AcyclicCount = Rem.CriticalPath * SchedModel->getLatencyFactor(); 0
3293 // InFlightCount = (AcyclicPath / IterCycles) * InstrPerLoop ----
3294 unsigned InFlightCount = 0
3295 (AcyclicCount * Rem.RemIssueCount + IterCount-1) / IterCount; 0
3296 unsigned BufferLimit = ----
3297 SchedModel->getMicroOpBufferSize() * SchedModel->getMicroOpFactor(); 0
3298 ----
3299 Rem.IsAcyclicLatencyLimited = InFlightCount > BufferLimit; 0
3300 ----
3301 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
3302 dbgs() << "IssueCycles=" ----
3303 << Rem.RemIssueCount / SchedModel->getLatencyFactor() << "c " ----
3304 << "IterCycles=" << IterCount / SchedModel->getLatencyFactor() ----
3305 << "c NumIters=" << (AcyclicCount + IterCount - 1) / IterCount ----
3306 << " InFlight=" << InFlightCount / SchedModel->getMicroOpFactor() ----
3307 << "m BufferLim=" << SchedModel->getMicroOpBufferSize() << "m\n"; ----
3308 if (Rem.IsAcyclicLatencyLimited) dbgs() << " ACYCLIC LATENCY LIMIT\n"); ----
3309 } ----

3311 void GenericScheduler::registerRoots() { 0
3312 Rem.CriticalPath = DAG->ExitSU.getDepth(); 0
3313 ----
3314 // Some roots may not feed into ExitSU. Check all of them in case. ----
3315 for (const SUnit *SU : Bot.Available) { 0
3316 if (SU->getDepth() > Rem.CriticalPath) 0
3317 Rem.CriticalPath = SU->getDepth(); 0
3318 } ----
3319 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Critical Path(GS-RR ): " << Rem.CriticalPath << '\n'); 0
3320 if (DumpCriticalPathLength) { 0
3321 errs() << "Critical Path(GS-RR ): " << Rem.CriticalPath << " \n"; 0
3322 } ----
3323 ----
3324 if (EnableCyclicPath && SchedModel->getMicroOpBufferSize() > 0) { 0
3325 Rem.CyclicCritPath = DAG->computeCyclicCriticalPath(); 0
3326 checkAcyclicLatency(); 0
3327 } ----
3328 } 0

3330 namespace llvm { ----
3331 bool tryPressure(const PressureChange &TryP, 0
3332 const PressureChange &CandP, ----
3333 GenericSchedulerBase::SchedCandidate &TryCand, ----
3334 GenericSchedulerBase::SchedCandidate &Cand, ----
3335 GenericSchedulerBase::CandReason Reason, ----
3336 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI, ----
3337 const MachineFunction &MF) { ----
3338 // If one candidate decreases and the other increases, go with it. ----
3339 // Invalid candidates have UnitInc==0. ----
3340 if (tryGreater(TryP.getUnitInc() < 0, CandP.getUnitInc() < 0, TryCand, Cand, 0
3341 Reason)) { ----
3342 return true; 0
3343 } ----
3344 // Do not compare the magnitude of pressure changes between top and bottom ----
3345 // boundary. ----
3346 if (Cand.AtTop != TryCand.AtTop) 0
3347 return false; 0
3348 ----
3349 // If both candidates affect the same set in the same boundary, go with the ----
3350 // smallest increase. ----
3351 unsigned TryPSet = TryP.getPSetOrMax(); 0
3352 unsigned CandPSet = CandP.getPSetOrMax(); 0
3353 if (TryPSet == CandPSet) { 0
3354 return tryLess(TryP.getUnitInc(), CandP.getUnitInc(), TryCand, Cand, 0
3355 Reason); 0
3356 } ----
3357 ----
3358 int TryRank = TryP.isValid() ? TRI->getRegPressureSetScore(MF, TryPSet) : 0
3359 std::numeric_limits::max(); 0
3360 ----
3361 int CandRank = CandP.isValid() ? TRI->getRegPressureSetScore(MF, CandPSet) : 0
3362 std::numeric_limits::max(); 0
3363 ----
3364 // If the candidates are decreasing pressure, reverse priority. ----
3365 if (TryP.getUnitInc() < 0) 0
3366 std::swap(TryRank, CandRank); 0
3367 return tryGreater(TryRank, CandRank, TryCand, Cand, Reason); 0
3368 } ----
3369 ----
3370 unsigned getWeakLeft(const SUnit *SU, bool isTop) { 0
3371 return (isTop) ? SU->WeakPredsLeft : SU->WeakSuccsLeft; 0
3372 } ----
3373 ----
3374 /// Minimize physical register live ranges. Regalloc wants them adjacent to ----
3375 /// their physreg def/use. ----
3376 /// ----
3377 /// FIXME: This is an unnecessary check on the critical path. Most are root/leaf ----
3378 /// copies which can be prescheduled. The rest (e.g. x86 MUL) could be bundled ----
3379 /// with the operation that produces or consumes the physreg. We'll do this when ----
3380 /// regalloc has support for parallel copies. ----
3381 int biasPhysReg(const SUnit *SU, bool isTop) { 0
3382 const MachineInstr *MI = SU->getInstr(); 0
3383 ----
3384 if (MI->isCopy()) { 0
3385 unsigned ScheduledOper = isTop ? 1 : 0; 0
3386 unsigned UnscheduledOper = isTop ? 0 : 1; 0
3387 // If we have already scheduled the physreg produce/consumer, immediately ----
3388 // schedule the copy. ----
3389 if (MI->getOperand(ScheduledOper).getReg().isPhysical()) 0
3390 return 1; 0
3391 // If the physreg is at the boundary, defer it. Otherwise schedule it ----
3392 // immediately to free the dependent. We can hoist the copy later. ----
3393 bool AtBoundary = isTop ? !SU->NumSuccsLeft : !SU->NumPredsLeft; 0
3394 if (MI->getOperand(UnscheduledOper).getReg().isPhysical()) 0
3395 return AtBoundary ? -1 : 1; 0
3396 } ----
3397 ----
3398 if (MI->isMoveImmediate()) { 0
3399 // If we have a move immediate and all successors have been assigned, bias ----
3400 // towards scheduling this later. Make sure all register defs are to ----
3401 // physical registers. ----
3402 bool DoBias = true; 0
3403 for (const MachineOperand &Op : MI->defs()) { 0
3404 if (Op.isReg() && !Op.getReg().isPhysical()) { 0
3405 DoBias = false; 0
3406 break; 0
3407 } ----
3408 } ----
3409 ----
3410 if (DoBias) 0
3411 return isTop ? -1 : 1; 0
3412 } ----
3413 ----
3414 return 0; 0
3415 } ----
3416 } // end namespace llvm ----
3417 ----
3418 void GenericScheduler::initCandidate(SchedCandidate &Cand, SUnit *SU, 0
3419 bool AtTop, ----
3420 const RegPressureTracker &RPTracker, ----
3421 RegPressureTracker &TempTracker) { ----
3422 Cand.SU = SU; 0
3423 Cand.AtTop = AtTop; 0
3424 if (DAG->isTrackingPressure()) { 0
3425 if (AtTop) { 0
3426 TempTracker.getMaxDownwardPressureDelta( 0
3427 Cand.SU->getInstr(), 0
3428 Cand.RPDelta, 0
3429 DAG->getRegionCriticalPSets(), 0
3430 DAG->getRegPressure().MaxSetPressure); 0
3431 } else { ----
3432 if (VerifyScheduling) { 0
3433 TempTracker.getMaxUpwardPressureDelta( 0
3434 Cand.SU->getInstr(), 0
3435 &DAG->getPressureDiff(Cand.SU), 0
3436 Cand.RPDelta, 0
3437 DAG->getRegionCriticalPSets(), 0
3438 DAG->getRegPressure().MaxSetPressure); 0
3439 } else { ----
3440 RPTracker.getUpwardPressureDelta( 0
3441 Cand.SU->getInstr(), 0
3442 DAG->getPressureDiff(Cand.SU), 0
3443 Cand.RPDelta, 0
3444 DAG->getRegionCriticalPSets(), 0
3445 DAG->getRegPressure().MaxSetPressure); 0
3446 } ----
3447 } ----
3448 } ----
3449 LLVM_DEBUG(if (Cand.RPDelta.Excess.isValid()) dbgs() 0
3450 << " Try SU(" << Cand.SU->NodeNum << ") " ----
3451 << TRI->getRegPressureSetName(Cand.RPDelta.Excess.getPSet()) << ":" ----
3452 << Cand.RPDelta.Excess.getUnitInc() << "\n"); ----
3453 } 0
3454 ----
3455 /// Apply a set of heuristics to a new candidate. Heuristics are currently ----
3456 /// hierarchical. This may be more efficient than a graduated cost model because ----
3457 /// we don't need to evaluate all aspects of the model for each node in the ----
3458 /// queue. But it's really done to make the heuristics easier to debug and ----
3459 /// statistically analyze. ----
3460 /// ----
3461 /// \param Cand provides the policy and current best candidate. ----
3462 /// \param TryCand refers to the next SUnit candidate, otherwise uninitialized. ----
3463 /// \param Zone describes the scheduled zone that we are extending, or nullptr ----
3464 /// if Cand is from a different zone than TryCand. ----
3465 /// \return \c true if TryCand is better than Cand (Reason is NOT NoCand) ----
3466 bool GenericScheduler::tryCandidate(SchedCandidate &Cand, 0
3467 SchedCandidate &TryCand, ----
3468 SchedBoundary *Zone) const { ----
3469 // Initialize the candidate if needed. ----
3470 if (!Cand.isValid()) { 0
3471 TryCand.Reason = NodeOrder; 0
3472 return true; 0
3473 } ----
3474 ----
3475 // Bias PhysReg Defs and copies to their uses and defined respectively. ----
3476 if (tryGreater(biasPhysReg(TryCand.SU, TryCand.AtTop), 0
3477 biasPhysReg(Cand.SU, Cand.AtTop), TryCand, Cand, PhysReg)) 0
3478 return TryCand.Reason != NoCand; 0
3479 ----
3480 // Avoid exceeding the target's limit. ----
3481 if (DAG->isTrackingPressure() && tryPressure(TryCand.RPDelta.Excess, 0
3482 Cand.RPDelta.Excess, 0
3483 TryCand, Cand, RegExcess, TRI, 0
3484 DAG->MF)) 0
3485 return TryCand.Reason != NoCand; 0
3486 ----
3487 // Avoid increasing the max critical pressure in the scheduled region. ----
3488 if (DAG->isTrackingPressure() && tryPressure(TryCand.RPDelta.CriticalMax, 0
3489 Cand.RPDelta.CriticalMax, 0
3490 TryCand, Cand, RegCritical, TRI, 0
3491 DAG->MF)) 0
3492 return TryCand.Reason != NoCand; 0
3493 ----
3494 // We only compare a subset of features when comparing nodes between ----
3495 // Top and Bottom boundary. Some properties are simply incomparable, in many ----
3496 // other instances we should only override the other boundary if something ----
3497 // is a clear good pick on one boundary. Skip heuristics that are more ----
3498 // "tie-breaking" in nature. ----
3499 bool SameBoundary = Zone != nullptr; 0
3500 if (SameBoundary) { 0
3501 // For loops that are acyclic path limited, aggressively schedule for ----
3502 // latency. Within an single cycle, whenever CurrMOps > 0, allow normal ----
3503 // heuristics to take precedence. ----
3504 if (Rem.IsAcyclicLatencyLimited && !Zone->getCurrMOps() && 0
3505 tryLatency(TryCand, Cand, *Zone)) 0
3506 return TryCand.Reason != NoCand; 0
3507 ----
3508 // Prioritize instructions that read unbuffered resources by stall cycles. ----
3509 if (tryLess(Zone->getLatencyStallCycles(TryCand.SU), 0
3510 Zone->getLatencyStallCycles(Cand.SU), TryCand, Cand, Stall)) 0
3511 return TryCand.Reason != NoCand; 0
3512 } ----
3513 ----
3514 // Keep clustered nodes together to encourage downstream peephole ----
3515 // optimizations which may reduce resource requirements. ----
3516 // ----
3517 // This is a best effort to set things up for a post-RA pass. Optimizations ----
3518 // like generating loads of multiple registers should ideally be done within ----
3519 // the scheduler pass by combining the loads during DAG postprocessing. ----
3520 const SUnit *CandNextClusterSU = ----
3521 Cand.AtTop ? DAG->getNextClusterSucc() : DAG->getNextClusterPred(); 0
3522 const SUnit *TryCandNextClusterSU = ----
3523 TryCand.AtTop ? DAG->getNextClusterSucc() : DAG->getNextClusterPred(); 0
3524 if (tryGreater(TryCand.SU == TryCandNextClusterSU, 0
3525 Cand.SU == CandNextClusterSU, 0
3526 TryCand, Cand, Cluster)) ----
3527 return TryCand.Reason != NoCand; 0
3528 ----
3529 if (SameBoundary) { 0
3530 // Weak edges are for clustering and other constraints. ----
3531 if (tryLess(getWeakLeft(TryCand.SU, TryCand.AtTop), 0
3532 getWeakLeft(Cand.SU, Cand.AtTop), 0
3533 TryCand, Cand, Weak)) ----
3534 return TryCand.Reason != NoCand; 0
3535 } ----
3536 ----
3537 // Avoid increasing the max pressure of the entire region. ----
3538 if (DAG->isTrackingPressure() && tryPressure(TryCand.RPDelta.CurrentMax, 0
3539 Cand.RPDelta.CurrentMax, 0
3540 TryCand, Cand, RegMax, TRI, 0
3541 DAG->MF)) 0
3542 return TryCand.Reason != NoCand; 0
3543 ----
3544 if (SameBoundary) { 0
3545 // Avoid critical resource consumption and balance the schedule. ----
3546 TryCand.initResourceDelta(DAG, SchedModel); 0
3547 if (tryLess(TryCand.ResDelta.CritResources, Cand.ResDelta.CritResources, 0
3548 TryCand, Cand, ResourceReduce)) ----
3549 return TryCand.Reason != NoCand; 0
3550 if (tryGreater(TryCand.ResDelta.DemandedResources, 0
3551 Cand.ResDelta.DemandedResources, 0
3552 TryCand, Cand, ResourceDemand)) ----
3553 return TryCand.Reason != NoCand; 0
3554 ----
3555 // Avoid serializing long latency dependence chains. ----
3556 // For acyclic path limited loops, latency was already checked above. ----
3557 if (!RegionPolicy.DisableLatencyHeuristic && TryCand.Policy.ReduceLatency && 0
3558 !Rem.IsAcyclicLatencyLimited && tryLatency(TryCand, Cand, *Zone)) 0
3559 return TryCand.Reason != NoCand; 0
3560 ----
3561 // Fall through to original instruction order. ----
3562 if ((Zone->isTop() && TryCand.SU->NodeNum < Cand.SU->NodeNum) 0
3563 || (!Zone->isTop() && TryCand.SU->NodeNum > Cand.SU->NodeNum)) { 0
3564 TryCand.Reason = NodeOrder; 0
3565 return true; 0
3566 } ----
3567 } ----
3568 ----
3569 return false; 0
3570 } ----
3571 ----
3572 /// Pick the best candidate from the queue. ----
3573 /// ----
3574 /// TODO: getMaxPressureDelta results can be mostly cached for each SUnit during ----
3575 /// DAG building. To adjust for the current scheduling location we need to ----
3576 /// maintain the number of vreg uses remaining to be top-scheduled. ----
3577 void GenericScheduler::pickNodeFromQueue(SchedBoundary &Zone, 0
3578 const CandPolicy &ZonePolicy, ----
3579 const RegPressureTracker &RPTracker, ----
3580 SchedCandidate &Cand) { ----
3581 // getMaxPressureDelta temporarily modifies the tracker. ----
3582 RegPressureTracker &TempTracker = const_cast(RPTracker); 0
3583 ----
3584 ReadyQueue &Q = Zone.Available; 0
3585 for (SUnit *SU : Q) { 0
3586 ----
3587 SchedCandidate TryCand(ZonePolicy); 0
3588 initCandidate(TryCand, SU, Zone.isTop(), RPTracker, TempTracker); 0
3589 // Pass SchedBoundary only when comparing nodes from the same boundary. ----
3590 SchedBoundary *ZoneArg = Cand.AtTop == TryCand.AtTop ? &Zone : nullptr; 0
3591 if (tryCandidate(Cand, TryCand, ZoneArg)) { 0
3592 // Initialize resource delta if needed in case future heuristics query it. ----
3593 if (TryCand.ResDelta == SchedResourceDelta()) 0
3594 TryCand.initResourceDelta(DAG, SchedModel); 0
3595 Cand.setBest(TryCand); 0
3596 LLVM_DEBUG(traceCandidate(Cand)); 0
3597 } ----
3598 } ----
3599 } 0
3600 ----
3601 /// Pick the best candidate node from either the top or bottom queue. ----
3602 SUnit *GenericScheduler::pickNodeBidirectional(bool &IsTopNode) { 0
3603 // Schedule as far as possible in the direction of no choice. This is most ----
3604 // efficient, but also provides the best heuristics for CriticalPSets. ----
3605 if (SUnit *SU = Bot.pickOnlyChoice()) { 0
3606 IsTopNode = false; 0
3607 tracePick(Only1, false); 0
3608 return SU; 0
3609 } ----
3610 if (SUnit *SU = Top.pickOnlyChoice()) { 0
3611 IsTopNode = true; 0
3612 tracePick(Only1, true); 0
3613 return SU; 0
3614 } ----
3615 // Set the bottom-up policy based on the state of the current bottom zone and ----
3616 // the instructions outside the zone, including the top zone. ----
3617 CandPolicy BotPolicy; 0
3618 setPolicy(BotPolicy, /*IsPostRA=*/false, Bot, &Top); 0
3619 // Set the top-down policy based on the state of the current top zone and ----
3620 // the instructions outside the zone, including the bottom zone. ----
3621 CandPolicy TopPolicy; 0
3622 setPolicy(TopPolicy, /*IsPostRA=*/false, Top, &Bot); 0
3623 ----
3624 // See if BotCand is still valid (because we previously scheduled from Top). ----
3625 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Picking from Bot:\n"); 0
3626 if (!BotCand.isValid() || BotCand.SU->isScheduled || 0
3627 BotCand.Policy != BotPolicy) { 0
3628 BotCand.reset(CandPolicy()); 0
3629 pickNodeFromQueue(Bot, BotPolicy, DAG->getBotRPTracker(), BotCand); 0
3630 assert(BotCand.Reason != NoCand && "failed to find the first candidate"); 0
3631 } else { ----
3632 LLVM_DEBUG(traceCandidate(BotCand)); 0
3633 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
3634 if (VerifyScheduling) { 0
3635 SchedCandidate TCand; 0
3636 TCand.reset(CandPolicy()); 0
3637 pickNodeFromQueue(Bot, BotPolicy, DAG->getBotRPTracker(), TCand); 0
3638 assert(TCand.SU == BotCand.SU && 0
3639 "Last pick result should correspond to re-picking right now"); ----
3640 } ----
3641 #endif ----
3642 } ----
3643 ----
3644 // Check if the top Q has a better candidate. ----
3645 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Picking from Top:\n"); 0
3646 if (!TopCand.isValid() || TopCand.SU->isScheduled || 0
3647 TopCand.Policy != TopPolicy) { 0
3648 TopCand.reset(CandPolicy()); 0
3649 pickNodeFromQueue(Top, TopPolicy, DAG->getTopRPTracker(), TopCand); 0
3650 assert(TopCand.Reason != NoCand && "failed to find the first candidate"); 0
3651 } else { ----
3652 LLVM_DEBUG(traceCandidate(TopCand)); 0
3653 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
3654 if (VerifyScheduling) { 0
3655 SchedCandidate TCand; 0
3656 TCand.reset(CandPolicy()); 0
3657 pickNodeFromQueue(Top, TopPolicy, DAG->getTopRPTracker(), TCand); 0
3658 assert(TCand.SU == TopCand.SU && 0
3659 "Last pick result should correspond to re-picking right now"); ----
3660 } ----
3661 #endif ----
3662 } ----
3663 ----
3664 // Pick best from BotCand and TopCand. ----
3665 assert(BotCand.isValid()); 0
3666 assert(TopCand.isValid()); 0
3667 SchedCandidate Cand = BotCand; 0
3668 TopCand.Reason = NoCand; 0
3669 if (tryCandidate(Cand, TopCand, nullptr)) { 0
3670 Cand.setBest(TopCand); 0
3671 LLVM_DEBUG(traceCandidate(Cand)); 0
3672 } ----
3673 ----
3674 IsTopNode = Cand.AtTop; 0
3675 tracePick(Cand); 0
3676 return Cand.SU; 0
3677 } ----
3678 ----
3679 /// Pick the best node to balance the schedule. Implements MachineSchedStrategy. ----
3680 SUnit *GenericScheduler::pickNode(bool &IsTopNode) { 0
3681 if (DAG->top() == DAG->bottom()) { 0
3682 assert(Top.Available.empty() && Top.Pending.empty() && 0
3683 Bot.Available.empty() && Bot.Pending.empty() && "ReadyQ garbage"); ----
3684 return nullptr; 0
3685 } ----
3686 SUnit *SU; ----
3687 do { ----
3688 if (RegionPolicy.OnlyTopDown) { 0
3689 SU = Top.pickOnlyChoice(); 0
3690 if (!SU) { 0
3691 CandPolicy NoPolicy; 0
3692 TopCand.reset(NoPolicy); 0
3693 pickNodeFromQueue(Top, NoPolicy, DAG->getTopRPTracker(), TopCand); 0
3694 assert(TopCand.Reason != NoCand && "failed to find a candidate"); 0
3695 tracePick(TopCand); 0
3696 SU = TopCand.SU; 0
3697 } ----
3698 IsTopNode = true; 0
3699 } else if (RegionPolicy.OnlyBottomUp) { 0
3700 SU = Bot.pickOnlyChoice(); 0
3701 if (!SU) { 0
3702 CandPolicy NoPolicy; 0
3703 BotCand.reset(NoPolicy); 0
3704 pickNodeFromQueue(Bot, NoPolicy, DAG->getBotRPTracker(), BotCand); 0
3705 assert(BotCand.Reason != NoCand && "failed to find a candidate"); 0
3706 tracePick(BotCand); 0
3707 SU = BotCand.SU; 0
3708 } ----
3709 IsTopNode = false; 0
3710 } else { ----
3711 SU = pickNodeBidirectional(IsTopNode); 0
3712 } ----
3713 } while (SU->isScheduled); 0
3714 ----
3715 if (SU->isTopReady()) 0
3716 Top.removeReady(SU); 0
3717 if (SU->isBottomReady()) 0
3718 Bot.removeReady(SU); 0
3719 ----
3720 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Scheduling SU(" << SU->NodeNum << ") " 0
3721 << *SU->getInstr()); ----
3722 return SU; 0
3723 } ----
3724 ----
3725 void GenericScheduler::reschedulePhysReg(SUnit *SU, bool isTop) { 0
3726 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertPos = SU->getInstr(); 0
3727 if (!isTop) 0
3728 ++InsertPos; 0
3729 SmallVectorImpl &Deps = isTop ? SU->Preds : SU->Succs; 0
3730 ----
3731 // Find already scheduled copies with a single physreg dependence and move ----
3732 // them just above the scheduled instruction. ----
3733 for (SDep &Dep : Deps) { 0
3734 if (Dep.getKind() != SDep::Data || 0
3735 !Register::isPhysicalRegister(Dep.getReg())) 0
3736 continue; 0
3737 SUnit *DepSU = Dep.getSUnit(); 0
3738 if (isTop ? DepSU->Succs.size() > 1 : DepSU->Preds.size() > 1) 0
3739 continue; 0
3740 MachineInstr *Copy = DepSU->getInstr(); 0
3741 if (!Copy->isCopy() && !Copy->isMoveImmediate()) 0
3742 continue; 0
3743 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Rescheduling physreg copy "; 0
3744 DAG->dumpNode(*Dep.getSUnit())); ----
3745 DAG->moveInstruction(Copy, InsertPos); 0
3746 } ----
3747 } 0
3748 ----
3749 /// Update the scheduler's state after scheduling a node. This is the same node ----
3750 /// that was just returned by pickNode(). However, ScheduleDAGMILive needs to ----
3751 /// update it's state based on the current cycle before MachineSchedStrategy ----
3752 /// does. ----
3753 /// ----
3754 /// FIXME: Eventually, we may bundle physreg copies rather than rescheduling ----
3755 /// them here. See comments in biasPhysReg. ----
3756 void GenericScheduler::schedNode(SUnit *SU, bool IsTopNode) { 0
3757 if (IsTopNode) { 0
3758 SU->TopReadyCycle = std::max(SU->TopReadyCycle, Top.getCurrCycle()); 0
3759 Top.bumpNode(SU); 0
3760 if (SU->hasPhysRegUses) 0
3761 reschedulePhysReg(SU, true); 0
3762 } else { ----
3763 SU->BotReadyCycle = std::max(SU->BotReadyCycle, Bot.getCurrCycle()); 0
3764 Bot.bumpNode(SU); 0
3765 if (SU->hasPhysRegDefs) 0
3766 reschedulePhysReg(SU, false); 0
3767 } ----
3768 } 0

3770 /// Create the standard converging machine scheduler. This will be used as the ----
3771 /// default scheduler if the target does not set a default. ----
3772 ScheduleDAGMILive *llvm::createGenericSchedLive(MachineSchedContext *C) { 0
3773 ScheduleDAGMILive *DAG = ----
3774 new ScheduleDAGMILive(C, std::make_unique(C)); 0
3775 // Register DAG post-processors. ----
3776 // ----
3777 // FIXME: extend the mutation API to allow earlier mutations to instantiate ----
3778 // data and pass it to later mutations. Have a single mutation that gathers ----
3779 // the interesting nodes in one pass. ----
3780 DAG->addMutation(createCopyConstrainDAGMutation(DAG->TII, DAG->TRI)); 0
3781 return DAG; 0
3782 } ----

3784 static ScheduleDAGInstrs *createConvergingSched(MachineSchedContext *C) { 0
3785 return createGenericSchedLive(C); 0
3786 } ----

3793 // PostGenericScheduler - Generic PostRA implementation of MachineSchedStrategy. ----

3796 void PostGenericScheduler::initialize(ScheduleDAGMI *Dag) { 0
3797 DAG = Dag; 0
3798 SchedModel = DAG->getSchedModel(); 0
3799 TRI = DAG->TRI; 0
3800 ----
3801 Rem.init(DAG, SchedModel); 0
3802 Top.init(DAG, SchedModel, &Rem); 0
3803 BotRoots.clear(); 0
3804 ----
3805 // Initialize the HazardRecognizers. If itineraries don't exist, are empty, ----
3806 // or are disabled, then these HazardRecs will be disabled. ----
3807 const InstrItineraryData *Itin = SchedModel->getInstrItineraries(); 0
3808 if (!Top.HazardRec) { 0
3809 Top.HazardRec = 0
3810 DAG->MF.getSubtarget().getInstrInfo()->CreateTargetMIHazardRecognizer( 0
3811 Itin, DAG); 0
3812 } ----
3813 } 0
3814 ----
3815 void PostGenericScheduler::registerRoots() { 0
3816 Rem.CriticalPath = DAG->ExitSU.getDepth(); 0
3817 ----
3818 // Some roots may not feed into ExitSU. Check all of them in case. ----
3819 for (const SUnit *SU : BotRoots) { 0
3820 if (SU->getDepth() > Rem.CriticalPath) 0
3821 Rem.CriticalPath = SU->getDepth(); 0
3822 } ----
3823 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Critical Path: (PGS-RR) " << Rem.CriticalPath << '\n'); 0
3824 if (DumpCriticalPathLength) { 0
3825 errs() << "Critical Path(PGS-RR ): " << Rem.CriticalPath << " \n"; 0
3826 } ----
3827 } 0
3828 ----
3829 /// Apply a set of heuristics to a new candidate for PostRA scheduling. ----
3830 /// ----
3831 /// \param Cand provides the policy and current best candidate. ----
3832 /// \param TryCand refers to the next SUnit candidate, otherwise uninitialized. ----
3833 /// \return \c true if TryCand is better than Cand (Reason is NOT NoCand) ----
3834 bool PostGenericScheduler::tryCandidate(SchedCandidate &Cand, 0
3835 SchedCandidate &TryCand) { ----
3836 // Initialize the candidate if needed. ----
3837 if (!Cand.isValid()) { 0
3838 TryCand.Reason = NodeOrder; 0
3839 return true; 0
3840 } ----
3841 ----
3842 // Prioritize instructions that read unbuffered resources by stall cycles. ----
3843 if (tryLess(Top.getLatencyStallCycles(TryCand.SU), 0
3844 Top.getLatencyStallCycles(Cand.SU), TryCand, Cand, Stall)) 0
3845 return TryCand.Reason != NoCand; 0
3846 ----
3847 // Keep clustered nodes together. ----
3848 if (tryGreater(TryCand.SU == DAG->getNextClusterSucc(), 0
3849 Cand.SU == DAG->getNextClusterSucc(), 0
3850 TryCand, Cand, Cluster)) ----
3851 return TryCand.Reason != NoCand; 0
3852 ----
3853 // Avoid critical resource consumption and balance the schedule. ----
3854 if (tryLess(TryCand.ResDelta.CritResources, Cand.ResDelta.CritResources, 0
3855 TryCand, Cand, ResourceReduce)) ----
3856 return TryCand.Reason != NoCand; 0
3857 if (tryGreater(TryCand.ResDelta.DemandedResources, 0
3858 Cand.ResDelta.DemandedResources, 0
3859 TryCand, Cand, ResourceDemand)) ----
3860 return TryCand.Reason != NoCand; 0
3861 ----
3862 // Avoid serializing long latency dependence chains. ----
3863 if (Cand.Policy.ReduceLatency && tryLatency(TryCand, Cand, Top)) { 0
3864 return TryCand.Reason != NoCand; 0
3865 } ----
3866 ----
3867 // Fall through to original instruction order. ----
3868 if (TryCand.SU->NodeNum < Cand.SU->NodeNum) { 0
3869 TryCand.Reason = NodeOrder; 0
3870 return true; 0
3871 } ----
3872 ----
3873 return false; 0
3874 } ----
3875 ----
3876 void PostGenericScheduler::pickNodeFromQueue(SchedCandidate &Cand) { 0
3877 ReadyQueue &Q = Top.Available; 0
3878 for (SUnit *SU : Q) { 0
3879 SchedCandidate TryCand(Cand.Policy); 0
3880 TryCand.SU = SU; 0
3881 TryCand.AtTop = true; 0
3882 TryCand.initResourceDelta(DAG, SchedModel); 0
3883 if (tryCandidate(Cand, TryCand)) { 0
3884 Cand.setBest(TryCand); 0
3885 LLVM_DEBUG(traceCandidate(Cand)); 0
3886 } ----
3887 } ----
3888 } 0
3889 ----
3890 /// Pick the next node to schedule. ----
3891 SUnit *PostGenericScheduler::pickNode(bool &IsTopNode) { 0
3892 if (DAG->top() == DAG->bottom()) { 0
3893 assert(Top.Available.empty() && Top.Pending.empty() && "ReadyQ garbage"); 0
3894 return nullptr; 0
3895 } ----
3896 SUnit *SU; ----
3897 do { ----
3898 SU = Top.pickOnlyChoice(); 0
3899 if (SU) { 0
3900 tracePick(Only1, true); 0
3901 } else { ----
3902 CandPolicy NoPolicy; 0
3903 SchedCandidate TopCand(NoPolicy); 0
3904 // Set the top-down policy based on the state of the current top zone and ----
3905 // the instructions outside the zone, including the bottom zone. ----
3906 setPolicy(TopCand.Policy, /*IsPostRA=*/true, Top, nullptr); 0
3907 pickNodeFromQueue(TopCand); 0
3908 assert(TopCand.Reason != NoCand && "failed to find a candidate"); 0
3909 tracePick(TopCand); 0
3910 SU = TopCand.SU; 0
3911 } ----
3912 } while (SU->isScheduled); 0
3913 ----
3914 IsTopNode = true; 0
3915 Top.removeReady(SU); 0
3916 ----
3917 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Scheduling SU(" << SU->NodeNum << ") " 0
3918 << *SU->getInstr()); ----
3919 return SU; 0
3920 } ----

3922 /// Called after ScheduleDAGMI has scheduled an instruction and updated ----
3923 /// scheduled/remaining flags in the DAG nodes. ----
3924 void PostGenericScheduler::schedNode(SUnit *SU, bool IsTopNode) { 0
3925 SU->TopReadyCycle = std::max(SU->TopReadyCycle, Top.getCurrCycle()); 0
3926 Top.bumpNode(SU); 0
3927 } 0

3929 ScheduleDAGMI *llvm::createGenericSchedPostRA(MachineSchedContext *C) { 0

3934 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
3935 // ILP Scheduler. Currently for experimental analysis of heuristics. ----
3936 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
3937 ----
3938 namespace { ----
3939 ----
3940 /// Order nodes by the ILP metric. ----
3941 struct ILPOrder { ----
3942 const SchedDFSResult *DFSResult = nullptr; ----
3943 const BitVector *ScheduledTrees = nullptr; ----
3944 bool MaximizeILP; ----
3945 ----
3946 ILPOrder(bool MaxILP) : MaximizeILP(MaxILP) {} 0
3947 ----
3948 /// Apply a less-than relation on node priority. ----
3949 /// ----
3950 /// (Return true if A comes after B in the Q.) ----
3951 bool operator()(const SUnit *A, const SUnit *B) const { 0
3952 unsigned SchedTreeA = DFSResult->getSubtreeID(A); 0
3953 unsigned SchedTreeB = DFSResult->getSubtreeID(B); 0
3954 if (SchedTreeA != SchedTreeB) { 0
3955 // Unscheduled trees have lower priority. ----
3956 if (ScheduledTrees->test(SchedTreeA) != ScheduledTrees->test(SchedTreeB)) 0
3957 return ScheduledTrees->test(SchedTreeB); 0
3958 ----
3959 // Trees with shallower connections have have lower priority. ----
3960 if (DFSResult->getSubtreeLevel(SchedTreeA) 0
3961 != DFSResult->getSubtreeLevel(SchedTreeB)) { 0
3962 return DFSResult->getSubtreeLevel(SchedTreeA) 0
3963 < DFSResult->getSubtreeLevel(SchedTreeB); 0
3964 } ----
3965 } ----
3966 if (MaximizeILP) 0
3967 return DFSResult->getILP(A) < DFSResult->getILP(B); 0
3968 else ----
3969 return DFSResult->getILP(A) > DFSResult->getILP(B); 0
3970 } ----
3971 }; ----
3972 ----
3973 /// Schedule based on the ILP metric. ----
3974 class ILPScheduler : public MachineSchedStrategy { ----
3975 ScheduleDAGMILive *DAG = nullptr; ----
3976 ILPOrder Cmp; ----
3977 ----
3978 std::vector ReadyQ; ----
3979 ----
3980 public: ----
3981 ILPScheduler(bool MaximizeILP) : Cmp(MaximizeILP) {} 0
3982 ----
3983 void initialize(ScheduleDAGMI *dag) override { 0
3984 assert(dag->hasVRegLiveness() && "ILPScheduler needs vreg liveness"); 0
3985 DAG = static_cast(dag); 0
3986 DAG->computeDFSResult(); 0
3987 Cmp.DFSResult = DAG->getDFSResult(); 0
3988 Cmp.ScheduledTrees = &DAG->getScheduledTrees(); 0
3989 ReadyQ.clear(); 0
3990 } 0
3991 ----
3992 void registerRoots() override { 0
3993 // Restore the heap in ReadyQ with the updated DFS results. ----
3994 std::make_heap(ReadyQ.begin(), ReadyQ.end(), Cmp); 0
3995 } 0

4059 /// Apply a less-than relation on the node order, which corresponds to the ----
4060 /// instruction order prior to scheduling. IsReverse implements greater-than. ----
4061 template ----
4062 struct SUnitOrder { ----
4063 bool operator()(SUnit *A, SUnit *B) const { 0
4064 if (IsReverse) ----
4065 return A->NodeNum > B->NodeNum; 0
4066 else ----
4067 return A->NodeNum < B->NodeNum; 0
4068 } ----
4069 }; ----
4070 ----
4071 /// Reorder instructions as much as possible. ----
4072 class InstructionShuffler : public MachineSchedStrategy { ----
4073 bool IsAlternating; ----
4074 bool IsTopDown; ----
4075 ----
4076 // Using a less-than relation (SUnitOrder) for the TopQ priority ----
4077 // gives nodes with a higher number higher priority causing the latest ----
4078 // instructions to be scheduled first. ----
4079 PriorityQueue, SUnitOrder> ----
4080 TopQ; ----
4081 ----
4082 // When scheduling bottom-up, use greater-than as the queue priority. ----
4083 PriorityQueue, SUnitOrder> ----
4084 BottomQ; ----
4085 ----
4086 public: ----
4087 InstructionShuffler(bool alternate, bool topdown) 0
4088 : IsAlternating(alternate), IsTopDown(topdown) {} 0
4089 ----
4090 void initialize(ScheduleDAGMI*) override { 0
4091 TopQ.clear(); 0
4092 BottomQ.clear(); 0
4093 } 0
4094 ----
4095 /// Implement MachineSchedStrategy interface. ----
4096 /// ----------------------------------------- ----
4097 ----
4098 SUnit *pickNode(bool &IsTopNode) override { 0
4099 SUnit *SU; ----
4100 if (IsTopDown) { 0
4101 do { ----
4102 if (TopQ.empty()) return nullptr; 0
4103 SU = TopQ.top(); 0
4104 TopQ.pop(); 0
4105 } while (SU->isScheduled); 0
4106 IsTopNode = true; 0
4107 } else { ----
4108 do { ----
4109 if (BottomQ.empty()) return nullptr; 0
4110 SU = BottomQ.top(); 0
4111 BottomQ.pop(); 0
4112 } while (SU->isScheduled); 0
4113 IsTopNode = false; 0
4114 } ----
4115 if (IsAlternating) 0
4116 IsTopDown = !IsTopDown; 0
4117 return SU; 0
4118 } ----
4119 ----
4120 void schedNode(SUnit *SU, bool IsTopNode) override {} 0
4121 ----
4122 void releaseTopNode(SUnit *SU) override { 0
4123 TopQ.push(SU); 0
4124 } 0
4125 void releaseBottomNode(SUnit *SU) override { 0
4126 BottomQ.push(SU); 0
4127 } 0
4128 }; ----
4129 ----
4130 } // end anonymous namespace ----
4131 ----
4132 static ScheduleDAGInstrs *createInstructionShuffler(MachineSchedContext *C) { 0
4133 bool Alternate = !ForceTopDown && !ForceBottomUp; 0
4134 bool TopDown = !ForceBottomUp; 0
4135 assert((TopDown || !ForceTopDown) && 0
4136 "-misched-topdown incompatible with -misched-bottomup"); ----
4137 return new ScheduleDAGMILive( ----
4138 C, std::make_unique(Alternate, TopDown)); 0
4139 } ----

4142 "shuffle", "Shuffle machine instructions alternating directions", ----
4143 createInstructionShuffler); ----

4236 /// Sort predicate for the intervals stored in an instance of ----
4237 /// ResourceSegments. Intervals are always disjoint (no intersection ----
4238 /// for any pairs of intervals), therefore we can sort the totality of ----
4239 /// the intervals by looking only at the left boundary. ----
4240 static bool sortIntervals(const ResourceSegments::IntervalTy &A, 0
4241 const ResourceSegments::IntervalTy &B) { ----
4242 return A.first < B.first; 0
4243 } ----
4244 ----
4245 unsigned ResourceSegments::getFirstAvailableAt( 0
4246 unsigned CurrCycle, unsigned StartAtCycle, unsigned Cycle, ----
4247 std::function ----
4248 IntervalBuilder) const { ----
4249 assert(std::is_sorted(std::begin(_Intervals), std::end(_Intervals), 0
4250 sortIntervals) && ----
4251 "Cannot execute on an un-sorted set of intervals."); ----
4252 unsigned RetCycle = CurrCycle; 0
4253 ResourceSegments::IntervalTy NewInterval = ----
4254 IntervalBuilder(RetCycle, StartAtCycle, Cycle); 0
4255 for (auto &Interval : _Intervals) { 0
4256 if (!intersects(NewInterval, Interval)) 0
4257 continue; 0
4258 ----
4259 // Move the interval right next to the top of the one it ----
4260 // intersects. ----
4261 assert(Interval.second > NewInterval.first && 0
4262 "Invalid intervals configuration."); ----
4263 RetCycle += (unsigned)Interval.second - (unsigned)NewInterval.first; 0
4264 NewInterval = IntervalBuilder(RetCycle, StartAtCycle, Cycle); 0
4265 } ----
4266 return RetCycle; 0
4267 } ----
4268 ----
4269 void ResourceSegments::add(ResourceSegments::IntervalTy A, 0
4270 const unsigned CutOff) { ----
4271 assert(A.first < A.second && "Cannot add empty resource usage"); 0
4272 assert(CutOff > 0 && "0-size interval history has no use."); 0
4273 assert(all_of(_Intervals, 0
4274 [&A](const ResourceSegments::IntervalTy &Interval) -> bool { ----
4275 return !intersects(A, Interval); ----
4276 }) && ----
4277 "A resource is being overwritten"); ----
4278 _Intervals.push_back(A); 0
4279 ----
4280 sortAndMerge(); 0
4281 ----
4282 // Do not keep the full history of the intervals, just the ----
4283 // latest #CutOff. ----
4284 while (_Intervals.size() > CutOff) 0
4285 _Intervals.pop_front(); 0
4286 } 0
4287 ----
4288 bool ResourceSegments::intersects(ResourceSegments::IntervalTy A, 0
4289 ResourceSegments::IntervalTy B) { ----
4290 assert(A.first <= A.second && "Invalid interval"); 0
4291 assert(B.first <= B.second && "Invalid interval"); 0
4292 ----
4293 // Share one boundary. ----
4294 if ((A.first == B.first) || (A.second == B.second)) 0
4295 return true; 0
4296 ----
4297 // full intersersect: [ *** ) B ----
4298 // [***) A ----
4299 if ((A.first > B.first) && (A.second < B.second)) 0
4300 return true; 0
4301 ----
4302 // right intersect: [ ***) B ----
4303 // [*** ) A ----
4304 if ((A.first > B.first) && (A.first < B.second) && (A.second > B.second)) 0
4305 return true; 0
4306 ----
4307 // left intersect: [*** ) B ----
4308 // [ ***) A ----
4309 if ((A.first < B.first) && (B.first < A.second) && (B.second > B.first)) 0
4310 return true; 0
4311 ----
4312 return false; 0
4313 } ----
4314 ----
4315 void ResourceSegments::sortAndMerge() { 0
4316 if (_Intervals.size() <= 1) 0
4317 return; 0
4318 ----
4319 // First sort the collection. ----
4320 _Intervals.sort(sortIntervals); 0
4321 ----
4322 // can use next because I have at least 2 elements in the list ----
4323 auto next = std::next(std::begin(_Intervals)); 0
4324 auto E = std::end(_Intervals); 0
4325 for (; next != E; ++next) { 0
4326 if (std::prev(next)->second >= next->first) { 0
4327 next->first = std::prev(next)->first; 0
4328 _Intervals.erase(std::prev(next)); 0
4329 continue; 0
4330 } ----
4331 } ----
4332 } ----
